(66, '11+ Tireless climbing experience, safe for beginners', '1709919547_66.png', '<p _msttexthash=\"42251573\" _msthash=\"363\" style=\"margin-block: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Climbing is a sport that is increasingly receiving love and excitement from many people from a variety of different age groups. However, for those who are just starting out, they should equip themselves with the necessary climbing experience, avoiding unwanted injuries or accidents.</p><p _msttexthash=\"4826822\" _msthash=\"364\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Let\'s take a look at Decathlon\'s 11+ climbing experiences for beginners in the article below!<br><br><br>﻿1. Exercise 2-4 weeks in advance</p><p _msttexthash=\"77338170\" _msthash=\"384\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Before climbing the mountain for 2-4 weeks, you need to focus on your physical training on the thigh and calf muscle groups to help you enhance the flexibility and endurance of your legs on the ramp terrain. At the same time, you should also pay attention to practicing back muscle groups to get used to carrying backpacks and heavy items on your back. Some physical exercises you can refer to are:</p><ul style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><li _msttexthash=\"41836249\" _msthash=\"385\">Jogging gently 3-4 days / week, every day maintaining a distance of 4-5 km at a speed of 5-6km / h (equivalent to pace ~ 12 minutes / km) to train leg muscles and heart rate. After a period of getting used to it, you can gradually increase the intensity of training to 4-5 days a week at a speed of 6-7km/h.</li><li _msttexthash=\"64707227\" _msthash=\"386\">Practice alternating jogging along with staircase climbing exercises. After a period of time getting used to the pace of training, it is possible to increase the difficulty of the exercise by wearing an additional backpack weighing 3-5kg to get used to the weight and slope of the distance. This helps you train your front thighs, leg muscles, and back muscles.</li><li _msttexthash=\"7476053\" _msthash=\"387\">Add some topical exercises such as leg flexion, standing up and sitting down to increase leg muscle group endurance.</li></ul><p _msttexthash=\"16869099\" _msthash=\"388\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">In addition to the exercise regimen, you also need to combine daily nutritional supplements with foods containing fiber and vitamins C and A in it to enhance the body\'s resistance.</p><figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full has-custom-border\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; clear: both; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); display: table;\" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"850\" height=\"478\" src=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/chay-bo-la-mot-trong-nhung-bai-tap-hieu-qua-de-ren-luyen-the-luc.jpg\" alt=\"Chạy bộ là một trong những bài tập hiệu quả để rèn luyện thể lực leo núi\" class=\"wp-image-3827\" srcset=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/chay-bo-la-mot-trong-nhung-bai-tap-hieu-qua-de-ren-luyen-the-luc.jpg 850w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/chay-bo-la-mot-trong-nhung-bai-tap-hieu-qua-de-ren-luyen-the-luc-300x169.jpg 300w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/chay-bo-la-mot-trong-nhung-bai-tap-hieu-qua-de-ren-luyen-the-luc-768x432.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\" _mstalt=\"40356602\" style=\"height: 592.439px; max-width: 100%; vertical-align: bottom; border-radius: 10px; width: 1053.5px;\"><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-top: 0.5em; caption-side: bottom; display: table-caption;\">Jogging is one of the effective exercises to train climbing strength</figcaption></figure><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"2_Tim_hieu_ky_ve_dia_hinh_va_thoi_tiet_cua_dia_diem_leo_nui\" _msttexthash=\"2842892\" _msthash=\"390\">2. Learn carefully about the terrain and weather of the climbing site</span></h2><p _msttexthash=\"18358782\" _msthash=\"391\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">By learning the characteristics of the weather and terrain of the climbing point, you can easily determine the route, convenient travel time or challenge according to your preferences.</p><p style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">For example: When exploring Ba Den mountain, you can know that there are hiking routes such as pagoda gate road, electricity pole road, Ma Thien Lanh street, White Stone road. While the pagoda gate road is the gate of the tourist area, going to the pagoda but there is a lot of garbage, the pole road is quite cool, There were many trees and there was passage through the information station of the troops.</p><p _msttexthash=\"93588287\" _msthash=\"393\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">In addition, this research also helps you customize and prepare more necessary climbing equipment according to the characteristics of the area. For example, in case the terrain is hilly, dense forest, luxuriant trees, you can prepare additional anti-squeeze sprays. If the climbing location is a sunny place, it is necessary to bring a lot of hat, sunscreen as well as plenty of water to replenish physical strength continuously.</p><p _msttexthash=\"7208890\" _msthash=\"394\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Especially, with climbing spots with difficult and complicated routes, you should ask local people to guide you.</p><p _msttexthash=\"62891907\" _msthash=\"395\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">A small suggestion, to be able to find out the terrain and weather characteristics of the climbing point in the most realistic and detailed way, you can refer to the information at the group such as \"Trekking Group, Climbing, Weekend Camping\", \"Trekking Enthusiast Association\" ,... or search for groups using the formula \"Climbing Review + Climbing Spot Name\".</p><figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full has-custom-border\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; clear: both; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); display: table;\" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"850\" height=\"478\" src=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/tim-hieu-dia-hinh-thoi-tiet-leo-nui.jpg\" alt=\"Tìm hiểu địa hình, thời tiết leo núi là một trong những kinh nghiệm leo núi quan trọng\" class=\"wp-image-3836\" srcset=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/tim-hieu-dia-hinh-thoi-tiet-leo-nui.jpg 850w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/tim-hieu-dia-hinh-thoi-tiet-leo-nui-300x169.jpg 300w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/tim-hieu-dia-hinh-thoi-tiet-leo-nui-768x432.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\" _mstalt=\"34420828\" style=\"height: 590.189px; max-width: 100%; vertical-align: bottom; border-radius: 10px; width: 1049.5px;\"><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-top: 0.5em; caption-side: bottom; display: table-caption;\">Understanding the terrain and weather climbing is one of the important climbing experiences</figcaption></figure><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"3_Hoc_cach_phan_bo_the_luc_cho_ca_hanh_trinh\" _msttexthash=\"1618981\" _msthash=\"397\">3. Learn to allocate fitness for the whole journey</span></h2><p _msttexthash=\"21046805\" _msthash=\"398\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">In order for your physical strength not to be lost quickly in the first stages of climbing, you need to move at a moderate speed, breathe regularly to limit shortness of breath and rapid loss of strength.</p><p _msttexthash=\"51812956\" _msthash=\"399\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">In addition, rest during movement is also essential for resuscitation. However, you should not rest for too long (longer than 15 minutes) to avoid cramps when continuing the journey. During this time, you can take advantage of more water, some snacks or take pictures with friends or explore the surrounding landscape.</p><figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full has-custom-border\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; clear: both; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); display: table;\" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"850\" height=\"566\" src=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/luon-phan-bo-the-luc-de-dam-bao-nang-luong.jpg\" alt=\"Hãy luôn phân bổ thể lực để đảm bảo năng lượng cho một chuyến hành trình dài \" class=\"wp-image-3835\" srcset=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/luon-phan-bo-the-luc-de-dam-bao-nang-luong.jpg 850w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/luon-phan-bo-the-luc-de-dam-bao-nang-luong-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/luon-phan-bo-the-luc-de-dam-bao-nang-luong-768x511.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\" _mstalt=\"33365683\" style=\"height: 691.519px; max-width: 100%; vertical-align: bottom; border-radius: 10px; object-fit: cover; width: 1038.5px;\"><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-top: 0.5em; caption-side: bottom; display: table-caption;\">Always allocate physical strength to ensure energy for a long journey</figcaption></figure><p _msttexthash=\"69018586\" _msthash=\"401\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">It is extremely important to ensure good fitness for the climb is that you should move closer to the starting point at least 1 night before the journey. Because after 1 long travel distance, the body needs time to recover before continuing to exercise vigorously. Especially for those who rarely travel by car, suffering from motion sickness, this is even more necessary.</p><p style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">For example: For Pusilung climbing, usually the travel time by car from Hanoi to the starting point in Muong Qi, Lai Chau is about 13-14 hours. Thus, in the process of moving to the climbing site alone, the backpackers have lost a lot of capacity and physical strength.</p><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"4_Chuan_bi_ky_va_dung_trang_phuc_dung_cu_leo_nui\" _msttexthash=\"2767401\" _msthash=\"403\">4. Prepare carefully and correctly climbing clothes and equipment</span></h2><p _msttexthash=\"6181357\" _msthash=\"404\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Comfortable, safe clothing are extremely important pieces to help you successfully conquer the peaks.</p><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; line-height: 1.4; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"41_Trang_phuc_leo_nui_nu_va_nam\" _msttexthash=\"1479907\" _msthash=\"405\">4.1. Women\'s and men\'s mountaineering clothing</span></h3><p _msttexthash=\"770835\" _msthash=\"406\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">For clothing, you should choose:</p><ul style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><li _msttexthash=\"6542380\" _msthash=\"407\">This type of clothing has the ability to absorb sweat, to easily regulate body temperature during movement.</li><li _msttexthash=\"21402186\" _msthash=\"408\">Two commonly chosen materials are polyester and nylon. You should not choose cotton material, although this is a material that absorbs sweat, but it dries for a long time and makes sweat cling to the body.</li><li _msttexthash=\"6305455\" _msthash=\"409\">In terms of color, you should choose clothes with bright colors, to reflect heat instead of absorbing heat.</li><li _msttexthash=\"5456386\" _msthash=\"410\">Choose outfits according to the multi-layered rule to match the changing weather during the move.</li></ul><p _msttexthash=\"2902146\" _msthash=\"411\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">For shoes, choose specialized climbing pairs depending on the route:</p><ul style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><li _msttexthash=\"5683431\" _msthash=\"412\">If you want to conquer rocky mountain roads, you should choose high-necked shoes with good friction.</li><li _msttexthash=\"9446944\" _msthash=\"413\">If the route involves crossing streams, waterfalls or wet terrain, you should choose waterproof shoes, specialized for trekking.</li></ul><figure class=\"wp-block-table\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; overflow-x: auto; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><p _msttexthash=\"1885312\" _msthash=\"414\" style=\"\">3 Important criteria for you when choosing hiking gear</p><li _msttexthash=\"2966301\" _msthash=\"415\" style=\"\">The fabric has good absorbency, dries quickly, does not stick to sweat.</li><li _msttexthash=\"862810\" _msthash=\"416\" style=\"\">Moderately wide size, easy to move.</li><li _msttexthash=\"1671969\" _msthash=\"417\" style=\"\">Clothes are durable, limiting tearing and fraying.</li></figure><p _msttexthash=\"22893923\" _msthash=\"418\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">In addition, other accessories such as hats, glasses, backpacks ,... is also essential for the climbing process. You can refer to more detailed outfit notes at: <a href=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/outfit-leo-nui\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" _istranslated=\"1\" style=\"\">Suggest 20+ safe climbing outfits, trendy</a> comfort.</p><figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full has-custom-border\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; clear: both; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); display: table;\" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"850\" height=\"567\" src=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/chuan-bi-trang-phuc-leo-nui-phu-hop.jpg\" alt=\"Chuẩn bị trang phục leo núi phù hợp giúp quá trình di chuyển của bạn trở nên dễ dàng hơnChuẩn bị trang phục leo núi phù hợp giúp quá trình di chuyển của bạn trở nên dễ dàng hơn\" class=\"wp-image-3828\" srcset=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/chuan-bi-trang-phuc-leo-nui-phu-hop.jpg 850w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/chuan-bi-trang-phuc-leo-nui-phu-hop-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/chuan-bi-trang-phuc-leo-nui-phu-hop-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\" _mstalt=\"156058227\" style=\"height: 692.741px; max-width: 100%; vertical-align: bottom; border-radius: 10px; width: 1038.5px;\"><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-top: 0.5em; caption-side: bottom; display: table-caption;\">Preparing the right climbing outfit makes your commute easier</figcaption></figure><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; line-height: 1.4; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"42_Dung_cu_leo_nui\" _msttexthash=\"469235\" _msthash=\"420\">4.2. Climbing equipment</span></h3><ul style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><li _msttexthash=\"12656722\" _msthash=\"421\">Flashlight, headlight: Help you illuminate the road, convenient to go at night, in the jungle. You can choose the type of lamp with the desired brightness.</li><li _msttexthash=\"4073446\" _msthash=\"422\">Hiking sticks: Support the force, help reduce body weight, increase climbing speed.</li><li _msttexthash=\"10628098\" _msthash=\"423\">Glove: You should choose one with suede, prickly wool, with felt lining, which prevents slipping, water repellency, creates good friction.</li><li _msttexthash=\"7583433\" _msthash=\"424\">Medicines, medical first aid kits: These include such types as antipyretic, insect repellent, individual bandages.</li><li _msttexthash=\"2931656\" _msthash=\"425\">Lighter: Use when lighting campfires, grilling food during climbing.</li><li _msttexthash=\"6043284\" _msthash=\"426\">Telephone: Help you call, save personal information, phone numbers of trusted people in case of danger.</li><li _msttexthash=\"5417334\" _msthash=\"427\">Compass: Assist you in finding your way and determining the direction to pitch your tent at night.</li></ul><p _msttexthash=\"2336633\" _msthash=\"428\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><br></p><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"5_Chi_mang_theo_nhung_do_thuc_su_can_thiet\" _msttexthash=\"1172834\" _msthash=\"429\">5. Bring only absolutely essential items</span></h2><p _msttexthash=\"27081392\" _msthash=\"430\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Carrying too many items will make you quickly deteriorate, hurt your shoulders and neck because the backpack is too heavy. This also increases the possibility of losing or dropping items, finding objects is also more difficult.</p><p _msttexthash=\"13468884\" _msthash=\"431\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">You should only bring some really necessary items including basic spare clothes, climbing gear and some items such as phones, power banks, hiking sticks, maps.</p><figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full has-custom-border\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; clear: both; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); display: table;\" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"850\" height=\"567\" src=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/chuan-bi-vua-du-nhung-vat-dung-can-thiet-leo-nui.jpg\" alt=\"Chuẩn bị vừa đủ những vật dụng cần thiết giúp hành trang leo núi của bạn nhỏ gọn, dễ di chuyển \" class=\"wp-image-3829\" srcset=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/chuan-bi-vua-du-nhung-vat-dung-can-thiet-leo-nui.jpg 850w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/chuan-bi-vua-du-nhung-vat-dung-can-thiet-leo-nui-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/chuan-bi-vua-du-nhung-vat-dung-can-thiet-leo-nui-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\" _mstalt=\"65825136\" style=\"height: 693.408px; max-width: 100%; vertical-align: bottom; border-radius: 10px; width: 1039.5px;\"><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-top: 0.5em; caption-side: bottom; display: table-caption;\">Prepare just enough necessary items to make your climbing luggage compact, easy to move </figcaption></figure><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"6_Hoc_cach_su_dung_cac_mon_do_va_ky_nang_sinh_ton_co_ban\" _msttexthash=\"1417312\" _msthash=\"433\">6. Learn to use basic items and survival skills</span></h2><p _msttexthash=\"54202122\" _msthash=\"434\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Cultivating climbing experience, you should not neglect to learn survival skills, skills to make your own water filter, skills to create fire sources, skills to repel insects, skills to tie ropes or alkali blood,... In addition, using some basic objects for survival skills is also important knowledge that cannot be ignored:</p><ul style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><li _msttexthash=\"11081031\" _msthash=\"435\">Compass: You need to learn how to adjust the bias, combine with the map for orientation, use compass azimuth, or measure azimuth based on the map.</li><li _msttexthash=\"5284383\" _msthash=\"436\">Map: You can have a paper map of the climbing terrain ready or use the map directions on Google Maps.</li></ul><figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full has-custom-border\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; clear: both; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); display: table;\" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"850\" height=\"567\" src=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hoc-cach-su-dung-la-ban.jpg\" alt=\"Học cách sử dụng la bàn là một trong những kỹ năng sinh tồn cần thiết khi đi leo núi\" class=\"wp-image-3831\" srcset=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hoc-cach-su-dung-la-ban.jpg 850w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hoc-cach-su-dung-la-ban-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hoc-cach-su-dung-la-ban-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\" _mstalt=\"35351615\" style=\"height: 699.411px; max-width: 100%; vertical-align: bottom; border-radius: 10px; width: 1048.5px;\"><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-top: 0.5em; caption-side: bottom; display: table-caption;\">Learning how to use a compass is one of the essential survival skills when hiking</figcaption></figure><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"7_Luon_tap_trung_va_chu_y_den_nguoi_di_cung\" _msttexthash=\"1771393\" _msthash=\"438\">7. Always focus and pay attention to your companions</span></h2><p _msttexthash=\"8943311\" _msthash=\"439\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">During the climb, you should go in a group or at least have 1 more companion if you need to separate the group to ensure your safety.</p><p _msttexthash=\"6704217\" _msthash=\"440\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">In addition, observing other team members also helps you promptly help in special situations and vice versa.</p><figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; clear: both; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); display: table;\" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"850\" height=\"567\" src=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/luon-chu-y-nhung-nguoi-di-cung.jpg\" alt=\"Luôn chú ý những người đi cùng để đảm bảo an toàn bản thân \" class=\"wp-image-3834\" srcset=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/luon-chu-y-nhung-nguoi-di-cung.jpg 850w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/luon-chu-y-nhung-nguoi-di-cung-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/luon-chu-y-nhung-nguoi-di-cung-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\" _mstalt=\"21414224\" style=\"height: 708.083px; max-width: 100%; vertical-align: bottom; width: 1061.5px;\"><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-top: 0.5em; caption-side: bottom; display: table-caption;\">Always pay attention to those traveling with you to ensure your own safety</figcaption></figure><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"8_Chia_se_ke_hoach_voi_nguoi_than\" _msttexthash=\"655421\" _msthash=\"442\">8. Share plans with relatives</span></h2><p _msttexthash=\"43458441\" _msthash=\"443\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Whether traveling alone or in a group, you will not avoid unexpected incidents, accidents, or simply the phone battery runs out, loses signal. Therefore, it is better to still inform your relatives about your trip. Although these are only worst-case scenarios, you should not be subjective.</p><p _msttexthash=\"27952548\" _msthash=\"444\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">This will help people know when you have an accident and contact rescuers when necessary. The information shared will also facilitate the work of the rescue team, thanks to timely notifications and being able to find you more easily.</p><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"9_Dung_xem_nhe_chung_so_do_cao\" _msttexthash=\"990574\" _msthash=\"445\">9. Do not take altitude phobia lightly</span></h2><p _msttexthash=\"30350021\" _msthash=\"446\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Fear of heights is a fairly common syndrome, estimated to occur in 2-5% of the population. Even if you do not plan to climb hills with steep slopes, at some point during the journey there may still be bridges or narrow walkways on steep hillsides.</p><p _msttexthash=\"20540715\" _msthash=\"447\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">If you suffer from acute fear of heights, choose routes that avoid such places. If you are traveling in a group, please share with other members about this to have support during the climbing process.</p><figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; clear: both; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); display: table;\" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"850\" height=\"567\" src=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hay-lua-chon-cac-cung-duong-de-di.jpg\" alt=\"Nếu bạn mắc chứng sợ độ cao, hãy lựa chọn các cung đường dễ đi và chia sẻ điều này với bạn đồng hành\" class=\"wp-image-3830\" srcset=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hay-lua-chon-cac-cung-duong-de-di.jpg 850w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hay-lua-chon-cac-cung-duong-de-di-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hay-lua-chon-cac-cung-duong-de-di-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\" _mstalt=\"68231384\" style=\"height: 692.074px; max-width: 100%; vertical-align: bottom; width: 1037.5px;\"><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-top: 0.5em; caption-side: bottom; display: table-caption;\">If you suffer from fear of heights, choose easy routes and share this with your companions</figcaption></figure><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"10_Hoc_cach_phong_ngua_con_trung\" _msttexthash=\"607503\" _msthash=\"449\">10. Learn to prevent insects</span></h2><p _msttexthash=\"25441897\" _msthash=\"450\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Hills and mountains are habitats for many large and small animals, especially insects. They can cause you small bites, itching or even allergies, burning pain. Here are some insects you should be careful about when hiking:</p><ul style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><li _msttexthash=\"57204134\" _msthash=\"451\">Bees and wasps: if stung by a bee, the sting should be treated immediately and avoid crushing the bee\'s carcass to avoid infusing additional toxins into the sting. After processing is complete, clean the burned area and apply ointment to soothe if necessary. This is also a trick that can be applied when hit by the sharp thorns of the plant.</li><li _msttexthash=\"31162924\" _msthash=\"452\">Mosquitoes: mosquitoes occur in the evening and are distributed mainly at altitudes between 600 and 2,200 m. Carry an insecticidal spray in the first-aid box. When you go to bed, pull the lock of the mosquito net in the tent to prevent mosquito bites.</li><li _msttexthash=\"25002679\" _msthash=\"453\">Grater: when squeezed too tightly, you can use thin-edged objects such as ATM cards or knives, combined with using salt or fire to squeeze out of the skin. Next, immediately rinse the wound with water or saline and bandage.</li><li _msttexthash=\"24108734\" _msthash=\"454\">Horse fly: this insect is often found in alpine meadows and around rivers. If bitten by a horsefly, immediately disinfect the bitten site (avoid pressing hard) and apply an anti-inflammatory cream to soothe the pain.</li><li _msttexthash=\"55610984\" _msthash=\"455\">Ticks: carriers of Lyme disease and live in certain forest areas, in areas of tall grass and with ferns. To prevent tick bites, you should wear light-colored trousers. At that time, you will easily detect ticks. If bitten, use picking tweezers to remove the bug. If you have a fever, you need to see a doctor immediately after you return.</li></ul><figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full has-custom-border\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; clear: both; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); display: table;\" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"850\" height=\"567\" src=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/trang-phuc-voi-ao-dai-tay-va-quan-dai-se-giup-ban-tranh-bi-con-trung-dot.jpg\" alt=\"Trang phục với áo dài tay và quần dài sẽ giúp bạn tránh bị côn trùng đốt\" class=\"wp-image-3837\" srcset=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/trang-phuc-voi-ao-dai-tay-va-quan-dai-se-giup-ban-tranh-bi-con-trung-dot.jpg 850w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/trang-phuc-voi-ao-dai-tay-va-quan-dai-se-giup-ban-tranh-bi-con-trung-dot-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/trang-phuc-voi-ao-dai-tay-va-quan-dai-se-giup-ban-tranh-bi-con-trung-dot-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\" _mstalt=\"28990988\" style=\"height: 700.078px; max-width: 100%; vertical-align: bottom; border-radius: 10px; width: 1049.5px;\"><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-top: 0.5em; caption-side: bottom; display: table-caption;\">Outfits with long-sleeved shirts and trousers will help you avoid insect bites</figcaption></figure><p _msttexthash=\"72707583\" _msthash=\"457\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">In addition, you also need to be fully vaccinated to avoid contracting diseases in mountainous forests such as dengue fever, malaria. During the climb, remember to wear long-sleeved clothes, thick fabrics and hats to minimize the sting and bite of the above insects. Besides, do not forget to prepare some drugs and aerosols against insects such as BullFrog, Avon ,... to use as needed.</p><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"11_Mot_so_tinh_huong_bat_ngo_khi_leo_nui_va_cach_xu_ly\" _msttexthash=\"3621800\" _msthash=\"458\">11. Some unexpected situations when climbing mountains and how to handle them</span></h2><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; line-height: 1.4; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"111_Khi_bi_cang_co_chuot_rut\" _msttexthash=\"795782\" _msthash=\"459\">11.1. With muscle tension, cramps</span></h3><p _msttexthash=\"11139427\" _msthash=\"460\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">In case you experience muscle tension, cramps, stretch your muscles gently, stretch your legs by standing upright, bend your legs at the knees.</p><p _msttexthash=\"33159412\" _msthash=\"461\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">At the same time, you can massage the cramped area with your hands to reduce muscle tension. Finally, if possible, you can apply a compress to the area with muscle tension, cramps, warm water bags, or warm towels to help the sore symptoms disappear quickly.</p><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; line-height: 1.4; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"112_Khi_bi_ran_can\" _msttexthash=\"534768\" _msthash=\"462\">11.2. When bitten by a snake</span></h3><p style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">If a snake is normal, there will only be small tooth marks in an arc, but if it is a poisonous snake, there will be 2 deep canine marks.</p><p style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">With the confirmed case of a venomous snake bite:</p><ul style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><li _msttexthash=\"14913665\" _msthash=\"465\">You need to remain calm, do not move, keep your arms/feet immobilized with bites, immediately contact a supporter and try to remember the characteristics of the snake.</li><li _msttexthash=\"7289919\" _msthash=\"466\">Wrap an elastic bandage around the bitten leg/arm (wrapped above the bite). CPR may be needed if breathing is present.</li><li _msttexthash=\"11264422\" _msthash=\"467\">When taken to a medical facility, describe the snake (color, size, shape,...) so that the doctor can identify and inject specific antivenom serum.</li></ul><p _msttexthash=\"867386\" _msthash=\"468\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">In the case of non-venomous snakes:</p><p _msttexthash=\"10068773\" _msthash=\"469\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">You still need to contact the helper to take you to a medical facility to be checked and monitored within at least 12 hours to ensure safety.</p><figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full has-custom-border\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; clear: both; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); display: table;\" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"850\" height=\"446\" src=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/khi-bi-ran-can-ban-can-binh-tinh-xu-ly.jpg\" alt=\"Khi bị rắn cắn, bạn cần bình tĩnh xử lý để đảm bảo an toàn\" class=\"wp-image-3832\" srcset=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/khi-bi-ran-can-ban-can-binh-tinh-xu-ly.jpg 850w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/khi-bi-ran-can-ban-can-binh-tinh-xu-ly-300x157.jpg 300w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/khi-bi-ran-can-ban-can-binh-tinh-xu-ly-768x403.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\" _mstalt=\"26152867\" style=\"height: 549.105px; max-width: 100%; vertical-align: bottom; border-radius: 10px; width: 1046.5px;\"><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\" _msttexthash=\"11403119\" _msthash=\"470\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-top: 0.5em; caption-side: bottom; display: table-caption;\">When bitten by a snake, you need to calmly handle it to ensure safety – Photo source: Internet</figcaption></figure><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; line-height: 1.4; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"113_Khi_bi_lac\" _msttexthash=\"397228\" _msthash=\"471\">11.3. When you get lost</span></h3><p _msttexthash=\"74532705\" _msthash=\"472\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">In the process of climbing, you will inevitably have rare cases when you get lost. If that is the case, you need to really calm down, locate where you are, mark lost places as well as leave messages for your teammates. Use communication and location navigation devices such as phones, compasses prepared to call your companions (if there is a signal location) or find a way out for yourself.</p><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"12_4_Sai_lam_nguoi_leo_nui_lan_dau_thuong_mac_phai\" _msttexthash=\"1360827\" _msthash=\"473\">12. 4 Mistakes first-time climbers often make</span></h2><p _msttexthash=\"6255964\" _msthash=\"474\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Here are some mistakes you need to keep in mind and absolutely avoid to ensure the quality of your journey:</p><ul style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><li _msttexthash=\"22484683\" _msthash=\"475\">Mistaking the peak height as equal to the climbing distance: For example, a peak with an altitude of 3000m does not mean that you only need to climb about 3km. But your total distance both up and down can be up to 25km.</li><li _msttexthash=\"4277975\" _msthash=\"476\">Choosing the wrong outfit: This can cause you to get injured during and after the climb.</li><li _msttexthash=\"7124910\" _msthash=\"477\">Carrying too many unnecessary supplies: Bulky, bulky luggage will drain you of your physical strength quickly.</li><li _msttexthash=\"8223995\" _msthash=\"478\">Overconfidence in fitness: This makes you overexert yourself and not have a proper schedule and rest time along the climb.</li></ul><figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full has-custom-border\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; clear: both; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); display: table;\" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"850\" height=\"567\" src=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/lua-chon-giay-leo-nui-khong-phu-hop.jpg\" alt=\"Lựa chọn giày leo núi không phù hợp là một trong những sai lầm nhiều người mắc phải\" class=\"wp-image-3833\" srcset=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/lua-chon-giay-leo-nui-khong-phu-hop.jpg 850w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/lua-chon-giay-leo-nui-khong-phu-hop-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/lua-chon-giay-leo-nui-khong-phu-hop-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\" _mstalt=\"49883262\" style=\"height: 692.074px; max-width: 100%; vertical-align: bottom; border-radius: 10px; width: 1037.5px;\"><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-top: 0.5em; caption-side: bottom; display: table-caption;\">Choosing the wrong hiking boots is one of the mistakes many people make</figcaption></figure><p style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Above is a summary of climbing experiencesthat need to lie in the heart of blood to help you have a smooth and safe journey. In particular, physical training and proper dress preparation are the most important factors.</p>', '2024-03-06', 0);
