(67, '[GUIDE] How to pack travel items into a backpack COMPACT, EASY TO GET', '1709919583_67.png', '<p _msttexthash=\"33374614\" _msthash=\"34\" style=\"margin-block: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" style=\"width: 1000px;\" data-filename=\"Veggie-mania-Pizza-Rau-Cu-Thap-Cam.jpg\"><br></p><p _msttexthash=\"33374614\" _msthash=\"34\" style=\"margin-block: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Preparing for a travel itinerary sometimes becomes a challenge when we try to pack everything into a limited-sized backpack. In this article, we\'ll share ways&nbsp;to pack travel items into backpacks&nbsp;that are smart&nbsp;, space-saving, and easy to pick up when needed.<br><br></p><p _msttexthash=\"28451319\" _msthash=\"188\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Cosmetics and personal items such as shower gel, shampoo, brushes, and razors should&nbsp;be placed in plastic bags with zippers. This method not only helps to avoid spills, but also makes it easier to see and retrieve the contents of the bag.</p><p _msttexthash=\"12297584\" _msthash=\"189\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Another trick is&nbsp;to put perfume and fragile bottles in socks.&nbsp;Then these socks should be placed between the types of clothing to ensure absolute safety.</p><p _msttexthash=\"37479988\" _msthash=\"190\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">With cloth hats, you can fold them just like clothes, but avoid putting too much stuff on the hat. Depending on your hat style, this may require adjustments to accommodate the concaveness and width of the hat. Avoid tucking too tightly, so that the hat does not stretch wide.</p><figure class=\"wp-block-table\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; overflow-x: auto; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size);\" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><br></figure><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"Buoc_1_Xep_lop_duoi_cung_cho_giay_dep_va_do_nang_kich_thuoc_lon\" _msttexthash=\"2885896\" _msthash=\"54\">Step 1: Lay out the bottom layer for heavy, large-sized shoes and items</span></h2><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; line-height: 1.4; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"Cach_xep_vat_dung_co_kich_thuoc_lon\" _msttexthash=\"690820\" _msthash=\"55\">How to stack large-sized items</span></h3><p _msttexthash=\"64606204\" _msthash=\"56\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">You can keep large items such as bags, books, notebooks neatly by&nbsp;putting them in a bag or tying them neatly.&nbsp;It is recommended to place heavy and little-used items&nbsp;at the bottom, near the back of the backpack. This is ideal for objects such as shoes, sleeping bags, or books, which increases stability and reduces pressure from gravity on your back and shoulders.</p><figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; clear: both; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); text-align: center; display: table; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"850\" height=\"567\" src=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/nen-dat-cac-vat-dung-co-trong-luong-lon-va-it-su-dung-o-phia-duoi.jpg\" alt=\"It is recommended to place heavy and little-used items at the bottom, near the back of the backpack\" class=\"wp-image-5871 note-float-right\" srcset=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/nen-dat-cac-vat-dung-co-trong-luong-lon-va-it-su-dung-o-phia-duoi.jpg 850w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/nen-dat-cac-vat-dung-co-trong-luong-lon-va-it-su-dung-o-phia-duoi-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/nen-dat-cac-vat-dung-co-trong-luong-lon-va-it-su-dung-o-phia-duoi-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\" _mstalt=\"51783888\" _msthash=\"57\" style=\"height: 1008.72px; max-width: 100%; vertical-align: bottom; width: 1512.2px; float: right;\"><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-top: 0.5em; caption-side: bottom; display: table-caption;\">It is recommended to place items with large weight and little use at the bottom, near the back of the backpack (Source: Internet)</figcaption></figure><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; line-height: 1.4; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"Cach_xep_giay_dep\" _msttexthash=\"294554\" _msthash=\"59\">How to stack shoes</span></h3><p _msttexthash=\"97628869\" _msthash=\"60\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">The most effective way to organize shoes is to&nbsp;place them in a special carrying bag and tightly attach the mouth&nbsp;of the bag to protect the shoes and prevent them from soiling other containers.&nbsp;Place your shoes near the wheel of your backpack, as they usually weigh the most. In this way, folding shoes in this position will help prevent the clutter of items during movement and make the process of opening and closing the backpack more convenient.</p><figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full has-custom-border\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; clear: both; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); display: table;\" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"850\" height=\"850\" src=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/de-giay-la-dat-chung-vao-tui-dung-dac-biet.jpg\" alt=\"The most effective way to organize shoes is to put them in a special carrying bag and tightly attach the mouth of the bag to protect the shoes and prevent them from soiling other containers \" class=\"wp-image-5869\" srcset=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/de-giay-la-dat-chung-vao-tui-dung-dac-biet.jpg 850w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/de-giay-la-dat-chung-vao-tui-dung-dac-biet-300x300.jpg 300w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/de-giay-la-dat-chung-vao-tui-dung-dac-biet-150x150.jpg 150w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/de-giay-la-dat-chung-vao-tui-dung-dac-biet-768x768.jpg 768w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/de-giay-la-dat-chung-vao-tui-dung-dac-biet-120x120.jpg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\" _mstalt=\"122497336\" _msthash=\"61\" style=\"height: 1524.2px; max-width: 100%; vertical-align: bottom; border-radius: 10px; width: 1524.2px;\"><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-top: 0.5em; caption-side: bottom; display: table-caption;\">The most effective way to organize shoes is to place them in a special carrying bag and tighten the mouth of the bag to protect the shoes and prevent them from soiling other containers&nbsp;</figcaption></figure><figure class=\"wp-block-table\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; overflow-x: auto; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><p _msttexthash=\"28451319\" _msthash=\"188\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><br></p></figure><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"Buoc_2_Xep_quan_ao_nhe_va_cac_do_dien_tu_vua_phai\" _msttexthash=\"1835054\" _msthash=\"72\">Step 2: Stack light clothes, and moderate electronics</span></h2><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; line-height: 1.4; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"Cach_xep_quan_ao_khoac_quan_dai\" _msttexthash=\"1031719\" _msthash=\"73\" style=\"font-size: 14px;\">How to fold clothes, jackets, trousers</span></h3><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; line-height: 1.4; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"Cach_xep_quan_ao_khoac_quan_dai\" _msttexthash=\"1031719\" _msthash=\"73\"><p _msttexthash=\"918801\" _msthash=\"74\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">How to fold a T-shirt is quite simple:</span></p><ul style=\"\"><li _msttexthash=\"2858310\" _msthash=\"75\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Place the shirt flat and stroke lightly to remove possible wrinkles.</span></li><li _msttexthash=\"6302335\" _msthash=\"76\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Fold about 6-8cm of the bear of the shirt to the top and bring the 2 sides of the sleeve to the inside of the body.</span></li><li _msttexthash=\"13643630\" _msthash=\"77\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Folding the back part of the shirt through the half and then folding the rest of the shirt overlapping helps to collapse the shirt by about 1/3 of its original size.</span></li><li _msttexthash=\"5775419\" _msthash=\"78\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Turn the shirt upside down so that the bear part is facing upwards and roll the shirt up from the collar.</span></li><li _msttexthash=\"2072681\" _msthash=\"79\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Finally, wrap the edge of the shirt to keep the roll secure.</span></li></ul><p _msttexthash=\"598975\" _msthash=\"80\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">For jackets with loose hats,</span></p><ul style=\"\"><li _msttexthash=\"1844947\" _msthash=\"81\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Remove the hat before starting the folding procedure.</span></li><li _msttexthash=\"2114606\" _msthash=\"82\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">If the hat cannot be removed, place the hat inside the shirt.</span></li><li _msttexthash=\"3962673\" _msthash=\"83\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Pull up the zipper and spread it flat before folding the sleeves diagonally inside.</span></li><li _msttexthash=\"3347942\" _msthash=\"84\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Bend the hem upwards by about 6-10cm and place the hat in the center of the coat.</span></li><li _msttexthash=\"1108367\" _msthash=\"85\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Roll the shirt in the same way as a T-shirt.</span></li></ul></span></h3><figure class=\"wp-block-table\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; overflow-x: auto; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"></figure><p _msttexthash=\"24827855\" _msthash=\"88\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">The second layer of backpack arrangement is for light items such as clothes and everyday items. In this layer, you should put trousers, skirts, and dresses.&nbsp;Fold clothes neatly and stack them in stacks to optimize space.</p><p _msttexthash=\"26736034\" _msthash=\"89\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">In the third layer, you need to stack thin and light clothes and accessories such as jewelry and belts. Organizing these items in the third layer makes it easy to search and retrieve without disturbing the items in your backpack.</p><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; line-height: 1.4; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"Cach_xep_do_lot_va_phu_kien\" _msttexthash=\"1052571\" _msthash=\"90\">How to stack underwear and accessories</span></h3><p style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">1 – Women\'s underwear</p><p _msttexthash=\"1394705\" _msthash=\"92\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">The method of folding underwear is as follows:</p><ul style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><li _msttexthash=\"1034956\" _msthash=\"93\" style=\"\">You need to spread your underwear flat.</li><li _msttexthash=\"3996941\" _msthash=\"94\" style=\"\">Perform the folding of underwear from the waistband of the pants to the crotch line.</li><li _msttexthash=\"2298556\" _msthash=\"95\" style=\"\">Turn the underwear upside down and perform a compact folding.</li><li _msttexthash=\"21763768\" _msthash=\"96\" style=\"\">Turn your pants upside down to make sure they are firm. Not only does it help maintain the good shape of your underwear, this folding method also helps you make the most of your backpack space when traveling.</li></ul><p _msttexthash=\"33977905\" _msthash=\"97\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">You can store your underwear neatly by placing them in a bag, or arranging them flat on the surface of your backpack (on top of the outer clothing) With the underwear folded quite small, you can rest assured that the backpack space will not take up too much space.</p><figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full has-custom-border\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; clear: both; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); display: table;\" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"850\" height=\"569\" src=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/cat-do-lot-vao-mot-tui.jpg\" alt=\"You can store your underwear neatly by placing them in a bag, or arranging them flat on the surface of your backpack (on top of outer clothing) \" class=\"wp-image-5866\" srcset=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/cat-do-lot-vao-mot-tui.jpg 850w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/cat-do-lot-vao-mot-tui-300x201.jpg 300w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/cat-do-lot-vao-mot-tui-768x514.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\" _mstalt=\"125337238\" _msthash=\"98\" style=\"height: 1020.32px; max-width: 100%; vertical-align: bottom; border-radius: 10px; width: 1524.2px;\"><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-top: 0.5em; caption-side: bottom; display: table-caption;\">You can store your underwear neatly by placing them in a bag, or arranging them flat on the surface of your backpack (on top of outer clothing) (Source: Internet)</figcaption></figure><p style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Shorts, shorts</p><p _msttexthash=\"18744752\" _msthash=\"101\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">These shorts and shorts are an&nbsp;indispensable&nbsp;option when we travel because of the comfort and convenience they offer. To avoid wrinkling, adhere to the following simple folding procedure:</p><ul style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><li _msttexthash=\"820625\" _msthash=\"102\" style=\"\">Fold the pants in half vertically.</li><li _msttexthash=\"819468\" _msthash=\"103\" style=\"\">Then, roll them round lengthwise.</li><li _msttexthash=\"2632812\" _msthash=\"104\" style=\"\">Use elastic bands to secure them or keep them neat in your backpack.</li></ul><p _msttexthash=\"5658705\" _msthash=\"105\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">You can also place shorts and shorts on the outer layer of clothing or right next to the underwear bag.</p><figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full has-custom-border\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; clear: both; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); display: table;\" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"850\" height=\"566\" src=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/quan-sooc-va-quan-dui-la-lua-chon-khong-the-thieu.jpg\" alt=\"Shorts and shorts are an indispensable option when we travel because of the comfort and convenience they offer \" class=\"wp-image-5872\" srcset=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/quan-sooc-va-quan-dui-la-lua-chon-khong-the-thieu.jpg 850w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/quan-sooc-va-quan-dui-la-lua-chon-khong-the-thieu-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/quan-sooc-va-quan-dui-la-lua-chon-khong-the-thieu-768x511.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\" _mstalt=\"87530482\" _msthash=\"106\" style=\"height: 996.293px; max-width: 100%; vertical-align: bottom; border-radius: 10px; width: 1496.2px;\"><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-top: 0.5em; caption-side: bottom; display: table-caption;\">Shorts and shorts are an indispensable choice when we travel because of the comfort and convenience they offer (Source: Internet)</figcaption></figure><p style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">For socks, gloves</p><p _msttexthash=\"27974141\" _msthash=\"109\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Small items like gloves and socks don\'t take up much space. You can put&nbsp;them in a small bag and stow them in a backpack in a corner right next to the underwear bag. Pay attention to how the socks are stowed according to the following method:</p><ul style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><li _msttexthash=\"2910726\" _msthash=\"110\" style=\"\">Roll the socks into a circle and use the sock neck itself to secure them.</li><li _msttexthash=\"903422\" _msthash=\"111\" style=\"\">Stow them in a corner of the backpack.</li></ul><figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full has-custom-border\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; clear: both; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); display: table;\" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"850\" height=\"810\" src=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/gang-tay-va-tat-chan-khong-chiem-nhieu-dien-tich.jpg\" alt=\"Small items like gloves and socks don\'t take up much space \" class=\"wp-image-5870\" srcset=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/gang-tay-va-tat-chan-khong-chiem-nhieu-dien-tich.jpg 850w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/gang-tay-va-tat-chan-khong-chiem-nhieu-dien-tich-300x286.jpg 300w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/gang-tay-va-tat-chan-khong-chiem-nhieu-dien-tich-768x732.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\" _mstalt=\"28967809\" _msthash=\"112\" style=\"height: 1432.46px; max-width: 100%; vertical-align: bottom; border-radius: 10px; width: 1503.2px;\"><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-top: 0.5em; caption-side: bottom; display: table-caption;\">Small items like gloves and socks don\'t take up much space (Source: Internet)</figcaption></figure><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; line-height: 1.4; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"Cach_xep_my_pham\" _msttexthash=\"424736\" _msthash=\"114\">How to stack cosmetics</span></h3><p _msttexthash=\"52055809\" _msthash=\"115\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Beauty products&nbsp;need to be tightly closed, and remember to&nbsp;wrap them with plastic bags&nbsp;to prevent liquid in cosmetics from leaking and harming clothes. Moreover, you should also break down cosmetics into small jars. It is not convenient to carry large and heavy cosmetic bottles and jars when traveling for several days.</p><figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full has-custom-border\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; clear: both; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); display: table;\" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"850\" height=\"850\" src=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/chia-nho-my-pham-vao-cac-lo-nho.jpg\" alt=\"You should also break down cosmetics into small jars to reduce the backpack area \" class=\"wp-image-5867\" srcset=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/chia-nho-my-pham-vao-cac-lo-nho.jpg 850w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/chia-nho-my-pham-vao-cac-lo-nho-300x300.jpg 300w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/chia-nho-my-pham-vao-cac-lo-nho-150x150.jpg 150w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/chia-nho-my-pham-vao-cac-lo-nho-768x768.jpg 768w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/chia-nho-my-pham-vao-cac-lo-nho-120x120.jpg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\" _mstalt=\"32657703\" _msthash=\"116\" style=\"height: 1509.2px; max-width: 100%; vertical-align: bottom; border-radius: 9px; width: 1509.2px;\"><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-top: 0.5em; caption-side: bottom; display: table-caption;\">You should also break down cosmetics into small jars to reduce the backpack area (Source: Internet)</figcaption></figure><figure class=\"wp-block-table\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; overflow-x: auto; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><br></figure><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"Buoc_3_Xep_cac_mon_do_nho_de_vo_vao_balo\" _msttexthash=\"1498601\" _msthash=\"148\">Step 3: Put small, fragile items in your backpack</span></h2><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; line-height: 1.4; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"Cach_xep_do_trang_suc_do_de_vo\" _msttexthash=\"881569\" _msthash=\"149\">How to stack jewelry, fragile items</span></h3><p _msttexthash=\"50369163\" _msthash=\"150\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">You can&nbsp;tie necklaces through straws and then put them back on.&nbsp;Repeat this process until you have attached a sufficient number of necklaces that you want to carry. Then, stack them neatly in a travel cosmetics bag. For earrings, temporarily skip the buttons and then put them back on. Put them in a travel underwear bag.</p><figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; clear: both; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); display: table;\" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"