(70, 'Unexpected benefits of climbing, hiking, trekking', '1709919677_70.png', '<p style=\"margin-block: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">What does climbing do? Not only helps to enhance physical and physical health, climbing activities also help to foster the spirit effectively, helping you become more positive every day. Let\'s explore the unexpected benefits of climbing, hiking and trekking with Decathlon in this article!<br><br><br>1. Benefits of climbing for the spirit</p><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; line-height: 1.4; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"11_Leo_nui_giup_ban_thu_gian_va_hanh_phuc_hon\">1.1. Climbing makes you more relaxed and happier</span></h3><p _msttexthash=\"49445318\" _msthash=\"48\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">According to a study by Professor Yoshifumi Miyazaki from Chiba University in Japan, people who are active outdoors feel more relaxed and happier. For example, when exercising in the forest, they reduce their stress levels through symptoms such as slower heart rate, lower blood pressure and cortisol levels.</p><p style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Besides, oxygen levels in the brain are also enhanced, thereby creating a positive impact on the health of climbers. </p><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; line-height: 1.4; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"12_Leo_nui_giup_tang_50_kha_nang_sang_tao\">1.2. Climbing increases creativity by 50%</span></h3><p _msttexthash=\"12795952\" _msthash=\"51\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">When immersed in open spaces with beautiful landscapes, the brain is stimulated. This effect will be further enhanced if you actively turn off your phone.</p><p style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><a href=\"https://archive.unews.utah.edu/news_releases/nature-nurtures-creativity-2/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" _mstmutation=\"1\" _istranslated=\"1\" style=\"\">Researchers from the Universities of Kansas and Utah</a> have even calculated that after a few days in nature without using a cell phone, creativity and problem-solving abilities increase by up to 50 percent. </p><figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized has-custom-border\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; clear: both; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); display: table;\" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/leo-nui-mang-lai-rat-nhieu-loi-ich-tinh-than.jpg\" alt=\"Climbing offers a lot of spiritual benefits\" class=\"wp-image-3726\" srcset=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/leo-nui-mang-lai-rat-nhieu-loi-ich-tinh-than.jpg 1920w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/leo-nui-mang-lai-rat-nhieu-loi-ich-tinh-than-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/leo-nui-mang-lai-rat-nhieu-loi-ich-tinh-than-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.decathlon.vn/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/leo-nui-mang-lai-rat-nhieu-loi-ich-tinh-than-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" _mstalt=\"14758653\" _msthash=\"53\" style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%; vertical-align: bottom; border-radius: 10px; width: 850px;\"><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-top: 0.5em; caption-side: bottom; display: table-caption;\">Climbing offers a lot of spiritual benefits</figcaption></figure><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"2_Loi_ich_cua_leo_nui_doi_voi_the_chat\">2. Benefits of climbing for physical fitness</span></h2><p _msttexthash=\"30405310\" _msthash=\"56\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">In addition to relaxing the mind and increasing creativity, the benefits of climbing, hiking and trekking include: boosting the immune system, maintaining muscles, reducing harmful cholesterol levels, reducing bone aging and weight loss.</p><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; line-height: 1.4; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"21_Leo_nui_giup_tang_cuong_he_mien_dich\">2.1. Climbing helps boost the immune system</span></h3><p _msttexthash=\"49572770\" _msthash=\"58\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Rock climbing is a moderate activity and does not require as much intensity as some other physical activities. When hiking in nature, climbers will benefit \"unconsciously\" from phytoncide molecules, a natural antibiotic secreted by plants. Thereby contributing to strengthening the overall immune system.</p><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; line-height: 1.4; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"22_Leo_nui_giup_duy_tri_co_bap\">2.2. Climbing helps maintain muscles</span></h3><p _msttexthash=\"39777205\" _msthash=\"60\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">You can go hiking, hiking for a long time without worrying about your body being overexerted. Since climbing is a form of holistic exercise, it focuses more on the muscles in the lower body without straining the joints. This is a great sport to maintain the firmness of the muscles.</p><p style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">To avoid affecting the joints when hiking, do not wear a backpack that is too heavy and pay attention to the even distribution of weight in the backpack. </p><figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter is-resized has-custom-border\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; clear: both; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); display: table;\" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://contents.mediadecathlon.com/p1781962/k$38a2ace4463f024c2ebb2de59ce76f3a/800x450/3120pt2306/6240xcr3510/loi-ich-cua-leo-nui.webp\" alt=\"Climbing Benefits\" _mstalt=\"1673061\" _msthash=\"62\" style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%; vertical-align: bottom; border-radius: 10px; width: 850px;\"></figure><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; line-height: 1.4; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"23_Leo_nui_giup_giam_nong_do_Cholesterol_co_hai\">2.3. Climbing helps reduce harmful cholesterol levels</span></h3><p _msttexthash=\"33297004\" _msthash=\"64\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Another effect of climbing is to reduce harmful cholesterol levels. Regular hiking helps minimize present cholesterol (LDL) levels and boost levels of beneficial cholesterol (HDL), thereby improving arterial health and reducing pressure on the heart.</p><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; line-height: 1.4; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"24_Leo_nui_giup_giam_lao_hoa_xuong\">2.4. Climbing helps reduce bone aging</span></h3><p _msttexthash=\"40464554\" _msthash=\"66\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Hiking also prevents osteoporosis by acting on the skeletal system. Bone density will be enhanced, thereby reducing the risk of fractures. You can also incorporate the use of extra <a href=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/vi/phu-kien-leo-nui/gay-leo-nui-12838?utm_source=blog&utm_medium=advice&utm_campaign=hiking_trekking_benefits\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" _istranslated=\"1\" style=\"\">hiking sticks</a> to reduce pressure on your knees as well as make climbing, uphill and downhill easier.</p><p _msttexthash=\"13008086\" _msthash=\"67\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Hiking helps the body synthesize vitamin D better thanks to exposure to the sun. Vitamin D will help to absorb calcium better and thus help strengthen bones.</p><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; line-height: 1.4; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"25_Leo_nui_giup_giam_can\">2.5. Climbing helps lose weight</span></h3><p _msttexthash=\"10206521\" _msthash=\"69\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Rock climbing can help burn between 300-600 calories for a one-hour trip, depending on the terrain, body weight, backpack weight, and speed.</p><figure class=\"wp-block-image is-resized has-custom-border\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://contents.mediadecathlon.com/p2050049/k$aba8cb6af4c695dac60d1304abedd8b2/800x450/3821pt2548/7642xcr4299/loi-ich-cua-viec-leo-nui.webp\" alt=\"Benefits of climbing\" _mstalt=\"4529382\" _msthash=\"70\" style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%; vertical-align: bottom; border-radius: 10px; width: 840px;\"></figure><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"Mot_vai_luu_y_khi_di_leo_nui_hiking\">A few notes when hiking, hiking</span></h2><p _msttexthash=\"48140534\" _msthash=\"72\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">As can be seen, the benefits of climbing are huge. Like all sporting activities, you should go hiking, hiking and trekking regularly to get the maximum benefits. The ideal hiking frequency is about 3 times / week, each time at least 30 million. If you go intermittently, the benefits will only last for 3 to 6 months.</p><p _msttexthash=\"29267732\" _msthash=\"73\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">If you are afraid that climbing in the wild will bring many risks, especially as a beginner, you can look to man-made climbing spots. Here, you will be able to train safely with the guidance of coaches and prepare your health for the real climb.</p><figure class=\"wp-block-image is-resized has-custom-border\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://contents.mediadecathlon.com/p2218908/k$5ed5186f90ceb413f550b507e3eddc08/800x450/1968pt1312/3936xcr2214/di-leo-nui.webp\" alt=\"What are the benefits of climbing\" _mstalt=\"2052193\" _msthash=\"74\" style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%; vertical-align: bottom; border-radius: 10px; width: 850px;\"></figure><p style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Final thoughts</p><p style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">When you have read this far, you probably already know what climbing does, right? As can be seen, the benefits of climbing and trekking for the body are huge. However, during the climb, you need to pay attention to the frequency and if you are a newbie, you should start by working with artificial climbing places.</p>', '2024-03-06', 0),
(71, 'Instructions on how to wear a backpack correctly to ensure safety and convenience', '1709919707_71.png', '<p _msttexthash=\"25856597\" _msthash=\"34\" style=\"margin-block: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">A backpack is a familiar accessory, but not everyone knows how to wear it. Let Decathlon share with you how to wear a backpack properly, ensuring no damage to bones and joints but still retaining its own convenience and style!<br><br><br><br><br><br></p><figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized has-custom-border\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; clear: both; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); display: table;\" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline;\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://contents.mediadecathlon.com/p2059583/k$92eef63fa4976ae3f21bbb2adf4493f3/3360pt2240/5973xcr4480/default.jpg\" alt=\"Wearing your backpack correctly helps protect your bones and joints while ensuring your own convenience and style\" _mstalt=\"45230705\" _msthash=\"35\" style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%; border-radius: 10px; width: 850px;\"></span></figure><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"Chon_balo_phu_hop_voi_muc_dich_va_co_the\" _msttexthash=\"1604941\" _msthash=\"47\">Choose the right backpack for the purpose and body</span></h2><p _msttexthash=\"37272248\" _msthash=\"48\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">With the use of storing things and being a basic fashion accessory, it is no surprise that on the market today there are many types of backpacks with many different designs, sizes, materials, serving different purposes. Basically, backpacks can be classified as follows:<br>      Daily backpack: Traditional school backpacks, laptop backpacks, mini backpacks, crossbody backpacks, leather backpacks<br>      Travel backpack: Carry-on backpacks, personal backpacks, backpacks with wheels, travel laptop backpacks, lightweight shoulder bags that can be folded<br>      Backpacking/trekking: Frameless backpacks, framed backpacks, military backpacks<br>      Sports backpacks: Drawstring backpacks, water storage backpacks, jogging backpacks, cycling backpacks, ski backpacks, hunting backpacks<br>      Multi-purpose backpack: Empty bags, backpacks, tote bags, handbag backpacks</p><p _msttexthash=\"55980925\" _msthash=\"54\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Accordingly, you need to determine what your purpose is when using a backpack to choose the right type of backpack. Once you have determined the type of backpack, base on the volume to be used and the body to choose the size of the backpack, personal preferences to choose the color and style, the environment used to choose the material.</p><div class=\"wp-block-buttons is-content-justification-center is-layout-flex wp-container-core-buttons-layout-1 wp-block-buttons-is-layout-flex\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; gap: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><div class=\"wp-block-button\" style=\"margin: 0px; display: inline-block;\"><br></div></div><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"Chi_tiet_cach_chinh_va_cach_deo_balo_dung\" _msttexthash=\"2357810\" _msthash=\"58\">Details on how to adjust and how to wear the backpack correctly</span></h2><p _msttexthash=\"36104991\" _msthash=\"59\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Once you have the right backpack, next learn how to wear it correctly. Although the design and function of each type of backpack are different, add and remove some details about the strap, but basically, you can apply the following steps to wear the backpack properly:</p><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; line-height: 1.4; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"Buoc_1_Khoac_balonbsplen_vai_noi_long_tat_ca_day_deo\" _msttexthash=\"2501954\" _msthash=\"60\">Step 1: Put the backpack on your shoulders, loosen all the straps</span></h3><p _msttexthash=\"6643195\" _msthash=\"61\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">This way, you can easily determine the comfort point without being affected by any factors before adjusting.</p><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; line-height: 1.4; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"Buoc_2_Siet_dai_hong_truoc\" _msttexthash=\"779493\" _msthash=\"62\">Step 2. Tighten the front hip belt</span></h3><p _msttexthash=\"50142170\" _msthash=\"63\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Place the hip belt on the lower abdomen and tighten until it feels firm enough. If the hip belt is tightened properly and in the right position, you will feel that the weight of the backpack on the shoulder area is significantly reduced. Therefore, this technique helps you keep strength when wearing a heavy backpack.</p><figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large has-custom-border\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline;\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://contents.mediadecathlon.com/s815102/k$37b407ade10cdb0448bf3e1a679b6063/800x450/2584pt1723/5168xcr2907/chinh-day-balo-dung-cach.jpg\" alt=\"tighten the front hip belt\" _mstalt=\"3493802\" _msthash=\"64\" style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%; border-radius: 20px;\"></span></figure><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; line-height: 1.4; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"Buoc_3_Dieu_chinh_quai_deo_balo\" _msttexthash=\"771589\" _msthash=\"65\">Step 3. Adjust the backpack strap</span></h3><p _msttexthash=\"34489104\" _msthash=\"66\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">A common mistake is to wear a backpack as high as possible. As such, the backpack weight will rest entirely on the shoulder area without being distributed between the shoulders and hips. When wearing, adjust so that the bottom of the backpack reaches the pelvis.</p><figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large has-custom-border\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline;\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://contents.mediadecathlon.com/s815103/k$841dd235629f1626d801b4eeb73c6e6b/800x449/2342pt1562/4685xcr2635/chinh-day-deo-balo-dung-cach.jpg\" alt=\"adjusting the backpack strap\" _mstalt=\"1250938\" _msthash=\"67\" style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%; border-radius: 20px;\"></span></figure><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; line-height: 1.4; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"Buoc_4_Dieu_chinh_balonbspo_vi_tri_phu_hop\" _msttexthash=\"1525381\" _msthash=\"68\">Step 4. Adjust the backpack in the right position</span></h3><p _msttexthash=\"15155218\" _msthash=\"69\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Some types of <a href=\"https://www.decathlon.vn/vi/p/8581384/tat-ca-san-pham/balo-trekking-mt500-air-6010-l-cho-nam-cam?utm_source=blog&utm_campaign=w33_How-To-Properly-Adjust-Your-Backpack-Straps\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" _istranslated=\"1\" style=\"\">backpacks allow height</a> adjustment to suit the shape. If the backpack is not an EASYFIT type, adjust the length of the back before adjusting the backpack strap.</p><figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large has-custom-border\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline;\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://contents.mediadecathlon.com/s815104/k$899ec560ff6683f2f3e966784de3d0be/800x450/2536pt1911/5072xcr2853/deo-balo-dung-cach.jpg\" alt=\"Backpack Wearing Guide\" _mstalt=\"2574091\" _msthash=\"70\" style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%; border-radius: 20px;\"></span></figure><p style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">WHAT IS THE EASYFIT SYSTEM?</p><p _msttexthash=\"9555936\" _msthash=\"72\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Decathlon\'s patented Easyfit system allows you to adjust back height and tension simultaneously by pulling the strap on each side.</p><ol style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><li _msttexthash=\"351663\" _msthash=\"73\">Put on your backpack</li><li _msttexthash=\"754494\" _msthash=\"74\">Fasten and tighten the hip strap</li><li _msttexthash=\"1310569\" _msthash=\"75\">Tighten the bands in order from top to bottom</li></ol><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; line-height: 1.4; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"Buoc_5_Siet_cac_dai_nho_tren_day_deo_vai\" _msttexthash=\"1745029\" _msthash=\"76\">Step 5. Tighten the small belts on the shoulder strap</span></h3><p _msttexthash=\"11740352\" _msthash=\"77\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">These straps are also known as backpack restraints. These straps help pull the backpack up close to the shoulders for greater comfort and firmness.</p><figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized has-custom-border\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline;\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://contents.mediadecathlon.com/s815105/k$b592%E2%80%A6%2520your%2520backpack.jpg?format=auto&quality=80\" alt=\"Wear your backpack correctly\" _mstalt=\"448604\" _msthash=\"78\" style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%; border-radius: 20px; width: 800px;\"></span></figure><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; line-height: 1.4; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"Buoc_6_Dieu_chinh_va_siet_dai_nguc_balo\" _msttexthash=\"1563549\" _msthash=\"79\">Step 6. Adjust and tighten the backpack chest belt</span></h3><p _msttexthash=\"12415156\" _msthash=\"80\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Note not to tighten the chest belt too tightly as this will interfere with breathing. The purpose of a chest belt is to keep the backpack stable as you move.</p><figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized has-custom-border\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline;\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://contents.mediadecathlon.com/s815099/k$d84d%E2%80%A6ckpack%2520-%2520chest.jpg?format=auto&quality=80\" alt=\"Wear your backpack correctly\" _mstalt=\"387504\" _msthash=\"81\" style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%; border-radius: 24px; width: 800px;\"></span></figure><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"Mot_vai_luu_y_de_deo_balo_dung_cach\" _msttexthash=\"1005095\" _msthash=\"82\">A few notes to wear a backpack properly</span></h2><p _msttexthash=\"10100272\" _msthash=\"83\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Besides choosing the backpack and adjusting the backpack in extreme detail above, Decathlon would like to note a few more things for you:</p><ul style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><li _msttexthash=\"2420119\" _msthash=\"84\">Wear the backpack with both straps, do not wear it off to the side</li><li _msttexthash=\"3444298\" _msthash=\"85\">Readjust the backpack strap when you wear clothes of different thicknesses</li><li _msttexthash=\"4422405\" _msthash=\"86\">Always use hip belts and chest belts with backpacks with strap designs in this position</li><li _msttexthash=\"4854655\" _msthash=\"87\">Don\'t wear your backpack too low, make sure the bottom of your backpack is at your waist level</li><li _msttexthash=\"3788018\" _msthash=\"88\">It is recommended to carry a backpack with a total weight of about 10% of body weight</li><li _msttexthash=\"16509974\" _msthash=\"89\">If you have to go long distances, the weight of the backpack should not exceed 20% of your body weight and you should use hiking shoes, hiking boots for the best support when moving</li></ul><figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large has-custom-border\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; clear: both; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); display: table;\" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline;\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://contents.mediadecathlon.com/p2177921/4847c1636a41aaef2c4217cbd5eb73582306f6ce38768a0e969cb431b0bc022c/mt-500-air-hiking-backpack-5010-l-men.jpg?format=auto\" alt=\"A few notes to wear a backpack properly\" _mstalt=\"3705793\" _msthash=\"90\" style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%; border-radius: 10px;\"></span><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-top: 0.5em; caption-side: bottom; display: table-caption;\">A few notes to wear a backpack properly</figcaption></figure><p _msttexthash=\"5135897\" _msthash=\"92\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Hope sharing about how to properly wear a backpack in extreme detail above will be useful to you!</p>', '2024-03-06', 0);
