(72, 'The secret to avoiding blisters when climbing, jogging', '1709919739_72.png', '<p class=\"gutenify-section-21d46a70-ff7c-11ed-a039-61f168e9e7c8\" _msttexthash=\"19998602\" _msthash=\"34\" style=\"margin-block: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">The blisters of the skin when participating in sports activities are too familiar to climbers and runners. Check out some tips from Decathlon to help you manage and prevent blisters while hiking!</p><figure class=\"wp-block-image gutenify-section-017cb110-ff7c-11ed-a039-61f168e9e7c8\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://contents.mediadecathlon.com/p1507679/k$31eea55771a50704cb4bbdf41dc5482b/1080x0/2784pt1851/5568xcr2784/default.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%; vertical-align: bottom;\"><br><br>Why does the skin blister hurt when climbing mountains or jogging or walking?</figure><p class=\"gutenify-section-017efb00-ff7c-11ed-a039-61f168e9e7c8\" _msttexthash=\"33157215\" _msthash=\"47\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">When climbing, painful blistering is usually caused by rubbing by socks, shoes, or small gravel, dirt/soil in the shoe. In addition, moisture (from sweat or external sources) is also a factor in blistering because moist skin will be soft and easier to rub.</p><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading gutenify-section-d56f39d0-ff7b-11ed-a039-61f168e9e7c8\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"Luon_thu_giay_truoc_khi_mua_hoac_it_nhat_la_truoc_khi_bat_dau_van_dong\">Always try on shoes before you buy, or at least before you start exercising</span></h2><p class=\"gutenify-section-4e669020-ff7e-11ed-a039-61f168e9e7c8\" _msttexthash=\"22408789\" _msthash=\"49\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Whether you buy shoes at the store, order online, don\'t forget to try them on and feel how comfortable they are. Put on your shoes and try walking on a variety of terrains such as flat ground, uphill and downhill.</p><p class=\"gutenify-section-7f4a0e90-ff80-11ed-a039-61f168e9e7c8\" _msttexthash=\"8573604\" _msthash=\"50\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Our Decathlon stores often have artificial slopes or miniature trails so you can try on shoes on different types of terrain).</p><p class=\"gutenify-section-69043900-ff7e-11ed-a039-61f168e9e7c8\" _msttexthash=\"7234357\" _msthash=\"51\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">If ordering online, choose a seller with a reasonable return policy so you can exchange shoes if it is not suitable.</p><div class=\"wp-block-buttons gutenify-section-79bb1e30-f858-11ed-a87e-fd00103a1422 is-content-justification-center is-layout-flex wp-container-core-buttons-layout-1 wp-block-buttons-is-layout-flex\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; gap: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><div class=\"wp-block-button gutenify-section-79d31300-f858-11ed-a87e-fd00103a1422\" style=\"margin: 0px; display: inline-block;\"><br></div></div><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading gutenify-section-8f54ceb0-ff80-11ed-a039-61f168e9e7c8\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"Dung_di_giay_moi_tren_nhung_cung_duong_dai\">Don\'t wear new shoes on long roads</span></h2><p class=\"gutenify-section-c135f8f0-ff80-11ed-a039-61f168e9e7c8\" _msttexthash=\"15630888\" _msthash=\"54\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">All new shoes are relatively stiff and need to be \"softened.\" So, wearing new shoes for long and rough roads can cause blisters on the skin of the feet, hindering your journey.</p><p class=\"gutenify-section-2e1eade0-ff81-11ed-a039-61f168e9e7c8\" _msttexthash=\"30975243\" _msthash=\"55\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Especially badger shoes need to be worn to soften (especially the skin) and hug your feet. The hard parts can rub against the skin and cause your feet to blister. The best way is to start on short and easy routes, then increase the distance gradually.</p><p class=\"gutenify-section-ccc32030-ff80-11ed-a039-61f168e9e7c8\" _msttexthash=\"21647353\" _msthash=\"56\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">You should also make sure that the shoe lining does not move when moving. This is especially important if there are additional shoe insoles to adjust shoe size or orthopedic insoles for medical purposes.</p><p class=\"gutenify-section-907145c0-ff81-11ed-a039-61f168e9e7c8\" _msttexthash=\"17134117\" _msthash=\"57\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Shoe insoles are usually designed for operation in urban environments and the lining surface is relatively glossy, which can cause your foot to slide inward and cause blistering.</p><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading gutenify-section-924a99a0-ff81-11ed-a039-61f168e9e7c8\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"Chon_tat_phu_hop_voi_ban_chan\">Choose the right socks for the feet</span></h2><p class=\"gutenify-section-c9014b50-ff82-11ed-a039-61f168e9e7c8\" _msttexthash=\"13023504\" _msthash=\"59\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Making sure socks are the right size is one of those important but easily overlooked details. A sock that doesn\'t fit well will shrink, leading to blistering.</p><p class=\"gutenify-section-c1b1a6b0-ff82-11ed-a039-61f168e9e7c8\" _msttexthash=\"26446446\" _msthash=\"60\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Pay close attention to the seams (even if they are very small) and make sure they don\'t rub or rub against the skin. Don\'t wear socks that are torn or too old because they have lost their ability to protect your feet or no longer fit.</p><p class=\"gutenify-section-e242bf90-ff82-11ed-a039-61f168e9e7c8\" _msttexthash=\"9368333\" _msthash=\"61\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Make sure to wear socks on your feet properly. For instance, make sure the heel of the sock matches your heel and isn\'t overstretched.</p><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading gutenify-section-e87115b0-ff82-11ed-a039-61f168e9e7c8\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"Thu_di_tat_va_giay_cung_luc\">Try on socks and shoes at the same time</span></h2><p class=\"gutenify-section-ea5ae450-ff82-11ed-a039-61f168e9e7c8\" _msttexthash=\"12814698\" _msthash=\"63\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">The socks that you are comfortable wearing with one shoe may not be comfortable to wear with another. That\'s because not all shoes are designed to be the same.</p><p class=\"gutenify-section-ed9f12d0-ff82-11ed-a039-61f168e9e7c8\" _msttexthash=\"29022422\" _msthash=\"64\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">There are many reasons for blistering. Common causes: the material used, the method of manufacture of shoes or designs specific to different sports. And depending on the shape of the shoe and the fit of the socks, some can cause blistering.</p><p class=\"gutenify-section-f083e340-ff82-11ed-a039-61f168e9e7c8\" _msttexthash=\"16737669\" _msthash=\"65\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Note the weather conditions of the place you are going to and choose the right pair of socks – shoes according to the season.</p><p class=\"gutenify-section-f300a310-ff82-11ed-a039-61f168e9e7c8\" _msttexthash=\"30392219\" _msthash=\"66\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Finally, remember that the way you tie your shoelaces also plays a part in ensuring your feet are properly fixed and not obtrusive. Do not hesitate to adjust your shoelaces according to how you feel when moving, especially when going downhill.</p><div class=\"wp-block-buttons gutenify-section-7052f9a0-ff86-11ed-a039-61f168e9e7c8 is-content-justification-center is-layout-flex wp-container-core-buttons-layout-2 wp-block-buttons-is-layout-flex\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; gap: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><div class=\"wp-block-button gutenify-section-7050fdd0-ff86-11ed-a039-61f168e9e7c8\" style=\"margin: 0px; display: inline-block;\"><br></div></div><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading gutenify-section-f5922360-ff82-11ed-a039-61f168e9e7c8\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span id=\"Giu_cho_ban_chan_kho_rao_va_am\">Keep feet dry and warm</span></h2><p class=\"gutenify-section-ff553900-ff82-11ed-a039-61f168e9e7c8\" _msttexthash=\"11252904\" _msthash=\"69\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">Foreign bodies (stones, sand, or bark) in shoes can also cause blisters. If they get inside your shoes, stop to take off your shoes and remove them.</p><p class=\"gutenify-section-0168fdd0-ff83-11ed-a039-61f168e9e7c8\" _msttexthash=\"53307774\" _msthash=\"70\" style=\"margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\">If you go on a picnic a few days in a row and only wear one pair of socks, make sure to keep them clean throughout the trip. It\'s better to bring 2 pairs of socks (even on short picnics) so you can change them if your feet get wet from stepping on a puddle or sudden rain. Remove the lining of your shoes and let them dry overnight if needed.</p><figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized gutenify-section-7342dbb0-ff88-11ed-a039-61f168e9e7c8\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; margin-block-start: var(--wp--preset--spacing--small); margin-block-end: 0px; max-width: var(--wp--style--global--content-size); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" oxygen-sans,=\"\" ubuntu,=\"\" cantarell,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" margin-left:=\"\" auto=\"\" !important;=\"\" margin-right:=\"\" !important;\"=\"\"><img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://contents.mediadecathlon.com/p1643828/k$009e9331f1d8a3e32f9b37a0e21b80c2/1180x0/2880pt2067/5760xcr2057/default.jpg?format=auto&quality=80\" alt=\"\" width=\"885\" height=\"316\" style=\"max-width: 100%; vertical-align: bottom; width: 100%;\"></figure>', '2024-03-06', 0),
(73, 'Notes to avoid risks when climbing', '1709919760_73.png', '<span _msttexthash=\"23304125\" _msthash=\"85\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-alternates: inherit; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-variant-position: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-optical-sizing: inherit; font-kerning: inherit; font-feature-settings: inherit; font-variation-settings: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Preparing and using climbing aids, obeying the rules of the team leader, choosing the path thoroughly and regularly monitoring the weather are things you should remember to avoid bad situations when climbing.<br><p _msttexthash=\"17262895\" _msthash=\"87\" style=\"font-variant-alternates: inherit; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-variant-position: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.6; font-optical-sizing: inherit; font-kerning: inherit; font-feature-settings: inherit; font-variation-settings: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Climbing is a popular tourist activity in Vietnam, often seen in backpacking teams, especially student groups. From November to May is an ideal time for people to schedule climbing.</p><p style=\"font-variant-alternates: inherit; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-variant-position: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.6; font-optical-sizing: inherit; font-kerning: inherit; font-feature-settings: inherit; font-variation-settings: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span _msttexthash=\"497965\" _msthash=\"88\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-alternates: inherit; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-variant-position: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-optical-sizing: inherit; font-kerning: inherit; font-feature-settings: inherit; font-variation-settings: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Prepare essential items</span></p><p _msttexthash=\"134502966\" _msthash=\"89\" style=\"font-variant-alternates: inherit; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-variant-position: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.6; font-optical-sizing: inherit; font-kerning: inherit; font-feature-settings: inherit; font-variation-settings: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Before each climbing journey, you need to know the items you need to prepare. In addition to medicines, first aid supplies, food, clothing ... You also have to prepare yourself the necessary equipment such as compass, vines, locators, sticks, flashlights, spare batteries, whistles, small knives ... In case of danger, you will definitely need to resort to it. Having time to prepare carefully, you should arrange them in easy-to-get places, and practice using them masterfully so as not to be embarrassed when using them.</p><p style=\"font-variant-alternates: inherit; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-variant-position: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.6; font-optical-sizing: inherit; font-kerning: inherit; font-feature-settings: inherit; font-variation-settings: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span _msttexthash=\"2021539\" _msthash=\"92\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-alternates: inherit; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-variant-position: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-optical-sizing: inherit; font-kerning: inherit; font-feature-settings: inherit; font-variation-settings: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Comply with the regulations of the head of the delegation</span></p><p _msttexthash=\"150013552\" _msthash=\"93\" style=\"font-variant-alternates: inherit; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-variant-position: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.6; font-optical-sizing: inherit; font-kerning: inherit; font-feature-settings: inherit; font-variation-settings: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">The person chosen to be the leader of the delegation must usually be the most knowledgeable and experienced person in the delegation. Therefore, you should listen attentively and follow their instructions (any stop signals, go fast or slow...) so that the journey ensures the safety of not one but everyone. In addition to safety, you can fully enjoy where you are going. Especially, do not separate the group, too slow or too fast compared to everyone in the group, leading to the leader of the group is difficult to control and the trip will be unhappy.</p><p style=\"font-variant-alternates: inherit; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-variant-position: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.6; font-optical-sizing: inherit; font-kerning: inherit; font-feature-settings: inherit; font-variation-settings: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span _msttexthash=\"2051803\" _msthash=\"94\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-alternates: inherit; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-variant-position: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-optical-sizing: inherit; font-kerning: inherit; font-feature-settings: inherit; font-variation-settings: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Choose your path thoroughly and improvise when climbing</span></p><p _msttexthash=\"183300585\" _msthash=\"95\" style=\"font-variant-alternates: inherit; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-variant-position: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.6; font-optical-sizing: inherit; font-kerning: inherit; font-feature-settings: inherit; font-variation-settings: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">In addition to careful research and scheduling, improvisation when choosing a path is also essential. It should be noted small but extremely important things such as following streams, marking roads ... When following the streamside path, you will easily have water to use if it runs out, in addition, in case you get lost, rescuers will also look in areas with water such as rivers, streams ... first. While walking, you have to remark the road to note the people behind as well as when you have to return if you encounter difficulties that cannot complete the journey such as injuries, fallen trees, mountains ...<br></p><p style=\"font-variant-alternates: inherit; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-variant-position: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.6; font-optical-sizing: inherit; font-kerning: inherit; font-feature-settings: inherit; font-variation-settings: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span _msttexthash=\"713622\" _msthash=\"99\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-alternates: inherit; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-variant-position: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-optical-sizing: inherit; font-kerning: inherit; font-feature-settings: inherit; font-variation-settings: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Regularly monitor the weather</span></p><p _msttexthash=\"80492061\" _msthash=\"100\" style=\"font-variant-alternates: inherit; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-variant-position: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.6; font-optical-sizing: inherit; font-kerning: inherit; font-feature-settings: inherit; font-variation-settings: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">The weather is the most direct and influential factor on the climb. Before you go, you must definitely look at the weather forecast or probe the situation. However, on the way to climb, you still have to regularly observe your surroundings to recognize the wind, wind direction, clouds, dew, insects ... That helps your teammates predict the change of weather (if any) to orient the path, stop or continue.</p></span>', '2024-03-06', 0),
(74, 'What is the concept of Trekking?', '1709919787_74.png', '<p _msttexthash=\"54904005\" _msthash=\"27\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\">As defined by Wikipedia, trekking is a form of walking for several days. Instead of choosing vehicles to move such as bicycles, motorbikes or cars, trekking participants will use only their feet to get around. The places that trekkers choose are often places far from the city, in the suburbs or roads with rough, pristine terrain.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></p><p _msttexthash=\"42384901\" _msthash=\"29\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\">In addition, go trekking is also a type of tourism, outdoor activities combined with camping and picnicking. Most trekking participants share the same hobby of exploring new places and being a bit adventurous. Trekkers will have to carry their necessary items with them during the trip.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></p><p _msttexthash=\"34298329\" _msthash=\"31\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\">The length of the trip will depend on each route, destination or decision of the trekker. A trekking trip will usually last for several days (about 2 days or more) so you will need to bring all the necessary items (the trekking gear section I will talk about below).</p><h2 style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.2em;\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Diem_khac_nhau_giua_leo_nui_hiking_va_trekking\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></span>The difference between climbing, hiking and trekking<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></span></h2><p _msttexthash=\"33381023\" _msthash=\"33\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\">However, a lot of people often mistakenly believe that Trekking vs Hiking is the same climbing. But in reality, these are completely different forms. To help you learn better, below we will distinguish the difference between climbing, hiking vs trekking?</p><h3 style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.4em;\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Trekking_voi_Hiking\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></span><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Trekking with Hiking</span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></span></h3><p _msttexthash=\"62283650\" _msthash=\"35\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\">To know the difference between Trekking vs Hiking, you first need to understand what is the concept of Go Hiking? Hiking is also an outdoor hiking activity. However, if trekking is walking in places with more diverse, rugged and challenging terrain, hiking is mostly on trails or asphalt. Thus, the first difference is in the characteristics of the road.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></p><p _msttexthash=\"45331988\" _msthash=\"37\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\">The next difference is in the number of travel days. As mentioned above, the number of days of a trekking trip is usually not limited, it can be days, weeks, months, and even years. However, this is the exact opposite of Hiking. Hiking is usually a scenic walk, so the day will usually be less than trekking.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></p><p _msttexthash=\"38347036\" _msthash=\"39\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\">The obvious difference between hiking and trekking is the intensity. Usually, when trekking you will have to move in many different types of terrain, be it trails, mud roads, cliff paths, steps, trekking through the forest or setting foot in places that they have never been.</p><p _msttexthash=\"13291759\" _msthash=\"40\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Therefore, the movements of trekkers are often more difficult and tiring. Requires you to prepare the necessary tools as well as acquire skills when moving.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></p><p _msttexthash=\"30397445\" _msthash=\"42\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Meanwhile, hikers often have a habit of sticking to an already existing route and they often do not move on an entirely new path. Perhaps that\'s why hiking trips are usually quite safe, suitable for those who are new to these outdoor activities.</p><h3 style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.4em;\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Trekking_voi_Leo_Nui\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></span><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Trekking with Climbing</span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></span></h3><p _msttexthash=\"38779624\" _msthash=\"44\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Many people often mistakenly believe that Trekking vs Climbing is the same activity. However, in reality, they are completely different. After learning what is the concept of Trekking above, surely you also know more about the nature and characteristics of Trekking, right?</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></p><p _msttexthash=\"30164446\" _msthash=\"46\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Compared to Trekking, Climbing is a sports activity where participants try to conquer the highest point of that mountain. Therefore, compared to Trekking, climbing requires you to have techniques as well as a very durable and supple health.</p><p _msttexthash=\"39840918\" _msthash=\"47\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\">The length of the trek will usually depend on the height of the mountain where you decide to visit, be it a day, 2 days, or several days. When climbing, participants will face different challenges such as trekking, climbing over large rocks or conquering heights where oxygen is low.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></p><p _msttexthash=\"33633795\" _msthash=\"49\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Trekking with Climbing will also have fundamentally different points. If you go trekking, you only need to prepare a few basic items such as backpacks, trekking shoes, trekking sticks ... then climbing the mountain will require ropes, helmets, seat belts ...</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></p><p _msttexthash=\"71532435\" _msthash=\"50\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Many people believe that Trekking is just an activity in climbing. That is not wrong because there are many climbing trips you will have to go through quite a long trekking distance to reach the top of the mountain. Compared to Trekking, climbing has many different types such as indoor climbing, sports climbing, to more advanced levels such as off-road climbing, rock climbing ...</p><h2 style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.2em;\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Di_Trekking_can_chuan_bi_nhung_gi\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></span>What to prepare for Trekking?<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></span></h2><p _msttexthash=\"14943318\" _msthash=\"52\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\">To have a more complete and perfect trip, in each trip you will need to prepare all the necessary items. Here is a list of important trekking items that are indispensable:</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Trekking boots:</p><ul style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 24px; padding: 0px;\"><li _msttexthash=\"16369912\" _msthash=\"55\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Depending on the terrain to choose a suitable pair of shoes. If the path is easy, you can use climbing boots. If you have to go underwater, amphibious trekking shoes will suit you.</li><li _msttexthash=\"10564203\" _msthash=\"56\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">In addition, if you mainly move at night, you should choose shoes with lights to ensure safety as well as help other members easily identify.</li></ul><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Prom trekking:</p><ul style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 24px; padding: 0px;\"><li _msttexthash=\"3829280\" _msthash=\"58\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">It is recommended to use power-assisted backpacks so as not to have shoulder pain</li><li _msttexthash=\"2751437\" _msthash=\"59\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">The interior design has a large capacity to easily store many items.</li></ul><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Apparel</p><ul style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 24px; padding: 0px;\"><li _msttexthash=\"1825382\" _msthash=\"61\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Waterproof jacket (windbreaker, ultra-light jacket)</li><li _msttexthash=\"1190969\" _msthash=\"62\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Long trekking pants, breathable material</li><li _msttexthash=\"5004948\" _msthash=\"63\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">It is recommended to wear long-form hiking pants for men and women, the material dries quickly</li></ul><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Food and drink</p><ul style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 24px; padding: 0px;\"><li _msttexthash=\"2777866\" _msthash=\"65\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Dry food: instant sausage, instant noodles, candy pastries, bread...</li><li _msttexthash=\"1591447\" _msthash=\"66\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Pre-prepared food (should be eaten on the same day)</li><li _msttexthash=\"2445313\" _msthash=\"67\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Drinking water: purified water, mineral saline, glucose water</li><li _msttexthash=\"388193\" _msthash=\"68\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Clean water purifier</li></ul><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Other items:</p><ul style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-left: 24px; padding: 0px;\"><li _msttexthash=\"209313\" _msthash=\"70\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Camping tents</li><li _msttexthash=\"175513\" _msthash=\"71\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Sleeping bag</li><li _msttexthash=\"283075\" _msthash=\"72\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Sleeping bag pads</li><li _msttexthash=\"537225\" _msthash=\"73\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Flashlight illumination</li><li _msttexthash=\"354536\" _msthash=\"74\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Grill and grate tray</li><li _msttexthash=\"209092\" _msthash=\"75\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Travel sheets</li><li _msttexthash=\"263497\" _msthash=\"76\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Trekking sticks</li><li _msttexthash=\"560131\" _msthash=\"77\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Maps, GPS navigation tools</li><li _msttexthash=\"389116\" _msthash=\"78\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Insecticidal sprays</li><li _msttexthash=\"160043\" _msthash=\"79\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Toiletries</li></ul>', '2024-03-06', 0),
