(1, 'Sherpa Climbing Teams', 'Mingma Sherpa', 'The Sherpa climbing teams in Nepal play a crucial role in the history and culture of mountaineering in the Himalayas, particularly in expeditions to Everest and other high peaks. The Sherpas are an ethnic minority primarily living in the northeastern region of Nepal, within and around the Himalayas. They are renowned for their strength, endurance, mountain knowledge, and exceptional climbing skills. This makes them indispensable guides and porters on mountaineering expeditions.\r\n\r\nDescription of Sherpa Climbing Teams\r\nExpertise and Skills: Sherpa members often have mountaineering experience from a very young age, developing survival and climbing skills over many generations. They are experts in assessing weather conditions, navigating in the mountains, and managing risks in treacherous terrains.\r\n\r\nRole in Expeditions: During expeditions, Sherpas perform various tasks including guiding, setting up camps, carrying logistics, and placing safety ropes. They also provide technical support, advice on acclimatization (the process of adjusting to altitude), and sometimes perform rescue operations.\r\n\r\nRespect and Discipline: Sherpa teams operate based on mutual respect, reverence for the mountains, and strict adherence to safety rules. They believe in respecting the mountains, considering the peaks as sacred places, and perform religious rituals before starting expeditions.\r\n\r\nCommunity and Economy: Participation in climbing teams provides an important source of income for the Sherpa community. Many families have a tradition of engaging in the mountaineering industry, with knowledge and experience passed from one generation to the next.\r\n\r\nChallenges and Risks: Despite high respect and excellent skills, the work of Sherpa teams carries high risks, including accidents, altitude sickness, and health issues related to high altitudes.\r\n\r\nSherpa climbing teams are not just mountain guides; they are explorers, protectors, and storytellers, offering the world a deep insight into one of the harshest environments on earth. They symbolize strength, bravery, and extraordinary spirit.', 'G.P.O. Box: 8739\r\nChahabil, Kathmandu, Nepal\r\n+977- 1-4486663, +977 9851070072\r\ninfo@sherpamountaineering.com', '1709891717_1.png', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m14!1m8!1m3!1d3532.0021465520686!2d85.35548!3d27.71722!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x39eb1bd7c71dbcc1%3A0x569c55088167003e!2sKumarigal%20Naya%20Marga%2C%20Kathmandu%2044600%2C%20Nepal!5e0!3m2!1svi!2sus!4v1708772993913!5m2!1svi!2sus\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe>', 0, 2),
(2, 'Japanese Alpine Club (JAC)', 'Masashi Kobayashi', 'The Japanese Alpine Club (JAC), founded in 1905, is the nation’s oldest and most prestigious mountaineering club. We take pride in the fact that　for more than a century the JAC has served mountaineering communities at home and abroad with a wide variety of activities and information. Countless overseas expeditions – including the historic conquering of 8,163-meter Mount Manaslu in the Himalayas in 1956 – are all part of the history of our organization, which has continuously strived to bring new perspectives to modern mountaineering.\r\nIn terms of organization, the JAC comprises of a headquarters office and 32 local sections. JAC headquarters is responsible for overall management of the club, including committees and numerous groups of members sharing common interests. The committees are charged with planning and executing programs that both align with the club’s philosophy and further its goals. A key undertaking is the Youth Club – an important pillar of JAC activity. Because we firmly believe that the future development of the mountaineering world relies on the growth and maturity of younger members, we intend to step up Youth Club-related programs – attracting more young mountaineers and providing them with a variety of priceless experiences.\r\nEach of the JAC’s 32 local sections conducts their own programs, providing JAC members in the area an opportunity to participate in activities as they wish. The great variety of local activities is yet another important pillar ensuring the ongoing vitality of the JAC.', 'Email:  jac-intl@jac.or.jp  \r\n5-4 Yonbancho, Chiyoda City, Tokyo 102-0081, Japan', '1709891800_2.png', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d50373.771468551124!2d139.6727014802224!3d35.67188463280639!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x60188c66af0153eb%3A0x1d1e022848f30a29!2sThe%20Japanese%20Alpine%20Club!5e1!3m2!1sen!2s!4v1708772645509!5m2!1sen!2s\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe>', 0, 3),
(3, 'Korean Alpine Federation (KAF)', 'Son Jung-ho', 'The Korean Alpine Federation (KAF) is one of the leading mountaineering organizations in South Korea, playing a crucial role in the development and promotion of mountaineering culture and sports in the country. Here are the details about KAF:\n\nHistory and Mission\n- Establishment:** KAF was established with the purpose of not only promoting the sport of mountaineering but also raising awareness and knowledge about mountain safety, nature conservation, and environmental preservation in high-altitude areas.\n- Mission: KAF is committed to developing the mountaineering community in South Korea through organizing training courses, workshops, and educational programs as well as conducting domestic and international expeditions.\n\nActivities and Programs\n- Training and Education: KAF offers courses on mountaineering techniques, mountain safety, and mountain rescue for both sport climbing and traditional mountaineering.\n- Expeditions and Trips: The organization regularly organizes and supports international mountaineering expeditions, aiming to conquer the world\'s highest peaks and promote the spirit of adventure.\n- Conservation and Environment:** KAF places a high priority on protecting the mountain environment and promoting conservation activities through educational campaigns and environmental protection initiatives.\n\nAchievements\n- Prominent Members:** KAF has many members who are renowned explorers and mountaineers, who have achieved international accomplishments and contributed to elevating South Korea\'s status in the global mountaineering community.\n- Events: KAF regularly organizes and participates in international mountaineering events, such as world climbing championships, mountaineering conferences, and climbing competitions, contributing to the development of the sport.\n\nSignificance\nKAF is not just a mountaineering organization; it is also a symbol of the spirit of exploration and love for nature in South Korea. Through its activities, KAF encourages people to understand and respect nature, while also developing themselves through sports and outdoor activities.\n\nDetailed information about specific programs, members, and events of KAF can be found on their official website or through newsletters and publications released by the organization.', 'Tel.02-414-2750 \nFax.02-419-1950\nEmail.kockaf@kaf.or.kr\nSeoul, Songpa-gu, Olympic-ro 424, SK Handball Stadium 106', '1.png', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3164.5998142128783!2d127.12622239999999!3d37.5173557!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x357cafd25920944b%3A0x45f02ffeed14aaf!2sSK%20Olympic%20Handball%20Stadium!5e0!3m2!1sen!2s!4v1709200343148!5m2!1sen!2s\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe>', 0, 4),
(4, 'Indian Mountaineering Foundation', 'President - Prof Harshwanti Bisht', 'Indian Mountaineering Foundation (IMF) is the apex national body for mountaineering and allied sports. What was initially formed as the \'Sponsoring Committee of the Cho Oyu Expedition\', transformed into the IMF on 5th January, 1961, as we know it today. IMF supports, promotes and regulates national and international climbing and mountaineering in India and is affiliated to the UIAA (International Mountaineering and Climbing Federation). IMF is also the regulatory body for the competitive Olympic sport of Sport Climbing and is affiliated to the IFSC (International Federation of Sport Climbing). IMF is also engaged in mountain protection work, knowledge building and creating awareness of the Indian Himalaya.', '6, Benito Juarez Marg, South Campus, South Moti Bagh, New Delhi, Delhi\nPhone Number: +9111-2411-1211', '1.png', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d108135.46657801849!2d77.09782576470785!3d28.586041904773964!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x390d1d0fc8210fe1%3A0x9768225daf7b59d4!2sIndian%20Mountaineering%20Foundation!5e0!3m2!1sen!2s!4v1708772462490!5m2!1sen!2s\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe>', 0, 5),
(5, 'Nepal Mountaineering Association (NMA)', 'Nima Nuru Sherpa', 'The Nepal Mountaineering Association (NMA) is a crucial organization in the field of mountaineering and exploration in Nepal. Established in 1973, the NMA is headquartered in Kathmandu, Nepal, and plays a significant role in managing and organizing mountaineering activities in the region. Here are some basic information and main missions of the NMA:\r\n\r\n Objectives and Missions:\r\n- Developing and Promoting Mountaineering and Exploration**: NMA works to develop mountaineering as a sport and a form of adventure tourism in Nepal.\r\n-Management and Licensing: The organization is responsible for licensing mountaineering expeditions to mountains not under the management of the Government of Nepal.\r\n- Safety and Training: NMA offers training courses on mountaineering techniques, mountain first aid, and safety for mountain guides and climbers.\r\n- Environmental Protection**: They are committed to protecting the mountain environment and promoting sustainable activities in mountaineering and tourism.\r\n\r\nPrograms and Activities:\r\n- Certification of Mountain Guides: NMA organizes training courses and certifies mountain guides, including the International Mountain Guides Association (UIAGM/IFMGA) program.\r\n- Management of \"Trekking Peaks\": NMA manages a number of mountains known as \"trekking peaks\" in Nepal, providing opportunities for explorers of all experience levels.\r\n- Promotion of Research and Conservation: The organization engages in research and conservation initiatives aimed at protecting the mountain environment and improving living conditions for local communities.\r\n\r\nMembership and Collaboration:\r\n- NMA is a member of international mountaineering organizations such as the Union Internationale des Associations d\'Alpinisme (UIAA) and maintains cooperative relations with many other mountaineering and exploration organizations worldwide.\r\n\r\nNMA plays an essential role in maintaining and managing Nepal\'s mountaineering traditions, enhancing safety, and promoting sustainable tourism. With its stature, NMA makes a significant contribution to the development of the global mountaineering community and the protection of Nepal\'s magnificent natural heritage.', 'Nagpokhari, Naxal, Kathmandu, Nepal\r\nPhone: +977-1-4534525, +977-1-4535442\r\nFax: +977-1-4534578\r\nEmail: office@nepalmountaineering.org or president@nepalmountaineering.org​​.', '1709891870_5.png', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3532.137973221858!2d85.32128007534672!3d27.71302597617938!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x39eb19058af6672d%3A0x437f359d3d43df23!2sNepal%20Mountaineering%20Association!5e0!3m2!1sen!2s!4v1708772494874!5m2!1sen!2s\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe>', 0, 2),
(6, 'Alpine Club of Pakistan', 'Col Manzoor Hussain', 'The Alpine Club of Pakistan (ACP) is the official national organization of Pakistan, responsible for the development of mountaineering and other mountain-related activities in the country. Established with the aim of promoting mountaineering culture, mountain safety, and environmental protection in Pakistan, the ACP plays a crucial role in supporting and managing mountaineering expeditions to some of the highest and most challenging mountains in the world, including K2, Nanga Parbat, and Gasherbrum.\r\n\r\nObjectives and Missions:\r\n- Developing Mountaineering and Exploration: ACP endeavors to develop mountaineering as a sport and encourages the exploration of high mountain regions in Pakistan.\r\n- Safety and Training: The organization provides training and guidance on mountaineering techniques, mountain first aid, and mountain safety for climbers and guides.\r\n- **Environmental Protection: ACP is committed to protecting the mountain environment and conducts environmental education programs for the mountaineering community and the public.\r\n\r\nPrograms and Activities:\r\n- Organizing Expeditions: ACP regularly organizes and supports mountaineering expeditions, both domestically and internationally.\r\n- International Cooperation: The organization works closely with international mountaineering clubs and exploration organizations to promote cultural exchange and mountaineering techniques.\r\n- Training Programs: ACP offers specialized training courses on mountaineering skills, first aid, and survival in harsh conditions.\r\n\r\n Membership and Affiliations:\r\n- ACP is a member of international mountaineering organizations such as the Union Internationale des Associations d\'Alpinisme (UIAA), which helps strengthen international relations and cooperation within the mountaineering community.\r\n\r\nFor more detailed information or to contact the Alpine Club of Pakistan, you can visit their official website or look for contact information directly through various media channels or social networks.', 'Jinnah Stadium, Pakistan Sports Complex, Kashmir Highway , Islamabad, Pakistan\r\nPhonei: 0092-51-9208963\r\nPhone: 0092 333 5383642, 0092 333 5176672\r\nFax: 0092-51-9244676,\r\nhttps://alpineclub.org.pk', '1709891923_6.png', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3319.2794041366037!2d73.0904946755879!3d33.70171837329089!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x38dfc193c6bcb9c9%3A0x52cb2015f815eff5!2sALPINE%20CLUB%20OF%20PAKISTAN!5e0!3m2!1sen!2s!4v1708772513502!5m2!1sen!2s\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe>', 0, 6),
(7, 'Alpine Association of Iran (AAI)', 'Mahdi Honarmand', 'The Alpine Association of Iran (AAI) is a non-profit organization dedicated to promoting mountaineering and outdoor activities in Iran. It provides resources and support for climbers, organizes expeditions, offers training programs, and advocates for environmental conservation in mountainous regions. The AAI also works to foster international cooperation in the field of mountaineering and coordinates with other alpine associations worldwide.', 'Tehran Province, Tehran, District 12, Darvazeh Dolat, Iran', '1709892763_18.png', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3240.008984103995!2d51.421887510493875!3d35.70139652875305!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x3f8e019713d5509f%3A0xd924bfcb331367bf!2sAlpine%20club%20of%20Iran!5e0!3m2!1svi!2s!4v1709892749817!5m2!1svi!2s\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe>', 0, 7),
(8, 'Hong Kong, China Mountaineering and Climbing Union Limited', 'CHAN Hon-tong, Jedi', 'The Mountain Climbing and Climbing Federation of Hong Kong, China Limited (formerly known as the Hong Kong Mountain Climbing Federation) was established in 1984. It is a regional representative organization for mountain climbing. It is also a sports federation and a funded organization recognized by the Hong Kong government. He is a member of the Mountain Alliance (UIAA), the Asian Mountaineering Federation (UAAA), the International Federation of Climbing (IFSC), the Asian Climbing Federation (IFSC-ACC), and a member of the Hong Kong Sports Federation and Olympic Committee (SF&OC).\r\nOur sports climbing team was officially established in 1992 and has been actively participating in many overseas competitions, including the Asian Championships, National Championships and World Cup events, and has achieved many successes. Hong Kong athletes have always performed well in sports climbing, and have achieved excellent results in the Asian Championships, National Championships and Asian Youth Championships many times; the cumulative number of medals has exceeded 250.', '<p>                                                                        One Stadium Path, Causeway, HongKong Room 1013, Olympic Building\r\n</p><p>Email: office@chkmcu.org.hk\r\n</p><p><a href=\"https://chkmcu.org.hk/hk/\" target=\"_blank\">https://chkmcu.org.hk/hk/</a>\r\n                                                                    </p>', '1.png', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3692.098139477921!2d114.18500997492767!3d22.274271979705293!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x3404005269b44ed5%3A0xec688ca9fa81b133!2sStadium%20Path%2C%20Hong%20Kong!5e0!3m2!1sen!2s!4v1709455578073!5m2!1sen!2s\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe>', 0, 8),
(9, 'Taiwan Mountaineering Association (TMA)', 'Huang Yiyuan', 'Taiwan Mountaineering Association (TMA) is a leading mountaineering and trekking organization in Taiwan. TMA was established with the goal of encouraging and developing mountain climbing, trekking, and nature exploration in and outside Taiwan. TMA\'s activities include organizing mountain climbing expeditions, training participants, protecting the mountain environment, and creating an exchange network among mountain lovers across Taiwan.\r\n\r\nTMA regularly offers training courses in climbing skills and safety, and organizes events such as climbing competitions, treks and expeditions. They also promote the values ​​of sustainable climbing and protecting the mountain environment.', 'No. 20, Zhulun St, Zhongshan District, Taipei City, Taiwan 10491\r\nhttps://www.tma.tw/', '1.png', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3614.8473707374696!2d121.5478874750202!3d25.039253277812982!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x3442abcf99e1e859%3A0x877039bdd20ffecb!2s9%2C%20No.%2029%2C%20Section%201%2C%20Anhe%20Rd%2C%20Da%E2%80%99an%20District%2C%20Taipei%20City%2C%20Taiwan%20106!5e0!3m2!1sen!2s!4v1709455491145!5m2!1sen!2s\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe>', 0, 9),
