(14, 'Bhutan Mountaineering Association (BMA)', 'Garab Dorji', 'Bhutan has recently garnered international recognition for the thrilling trekking and adventure experiences it offers to anyone who travels to the country. Trekking is the best way to see Bhutan’s changing landscape against the backdrop of perpetual snow-capped mountains, pristine trails leading through the Himalayan wilderness full of exotic species of flora and fauna\r\n\r\nTrekking in Bhutan has secured its standing as one of the best adventures to be experienced in the world. Bear Grylls, the famous adventurer and survivalist listed Bhutan as one of the top 10 adventure travel destinations in the world. Furthermore, trekking adventures such as the Snowman Trek, Snowman run, and Tergola Trek are acclaimed by Lonely Planet, Times Magazine, Forbes and CNN among many other unique trekking experiences in Bhutan.\r\n\r\nFrom simple day long hikes to the popular eight-day Jumolhari, twelve-day Laya Gasa Trek and the fascinating 23-day Snowman Trek – Bhutan has a trek to suit every interest. Bhutan\r\nis a land of adventure, history, wonder and mysticism and trekking in Bhutan unites all these facets seamlessly.', '<p> Lhaki Complex, Phendey Lam, PO Box 125, Thimphu:Bhutan </p><p>Tel:+975 02 339864, fax:+975 02 331666</p><p> Email: ictmanagertj@gmail.com\r\n                                        </p>', '1709893779_22.png', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d169706.61190604998!2d89.58237092004505!3d27.483291138438688!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x39e1959e19f0fc67%3A0xc40d91ff2854ed19!2sBhutan%20Amateur%20Athletic%20Federation!5e0!3m2!1svi!2s!4v1709893750456!5m2!1svi!2s\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe>', 0, 11),
(15, 'Malaysian National Mountaineering Association (MNMA)', 'MOHD ZAIDI B. HJ KAMARUDDIN', 'The Malaysian National Mountaineering Association (MNMA), also known as Persatuan Mendaki Malaysia in Malay, is the national governing body for mountaineering and climbing activities in Malaysia. This association is likely responsible for the promotion, development, and regulation of mountaineering and climbing sports across the country. It could be involved in various activities such as organizing climbing expeditions, setting safety standards, providing training and certifications for climbers and instructors, and representing Malaysia in international climbing and mountaineering federations.\r\n\r\nMNMA may also play a critical role in environmental conservation efforts related to mountainous areas, advocating for sustainable practices among climbers and mountaineers. Additionally, the association could be involved in community outreach, aiming to increase participation and interest in the sport among Malaysians of all ages.\r\n\r\nGiven the nature of such organizations, MNMA would likely be a member of the International Climbing and Mountaineering Federation (UIAA), aligning its standards and practices with international guidelines to ensure safety and promote the sport globally.\r\n\r\nFor the most current information about the MNMA, including its programs, membership details, and upcoming events, visiting the official website or contacting the association directly would provide the most accurate and up-to-date information.', '<p>Jabatan Belia dan Sukan, W.P Kuala Lumpur,\r\nBukit Kiara 60000</p><p>(+60) 12-321 0400\r\n</p><p>Email: info@pmm-climbing.org.my\r\n                                        </p>', '1709629776_23.png', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3983.82800411208!2d101.64292507483484!3d3.1400769968353646!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x31cc4910de43e997%3A0x94260bbb81ee6339!2sJabatan%20Belia%20%26%20Suk