(17, 'Afghanistan Mountaineering Federation (AMF)', 'Sirat', 'The Afghanistan Mountaineering Federation (AMF) is an organization focused on promoting mountaineering and climbing sports in Afghanistan. While specific details about the AMF\'s founding date, key figures, and full scope of activities might vary, such organizations typically aim to develop mountaineering skills among locals, support the exploration and conservation of the country\'s mountainous regions, and represent Afghanistan in the international mountaineering community.\r\n\r\nGiven Afghanistan\'s rugged terrain and significant mountain ranges, including parts of the Himalayas, the Hindu Kush, and the Pamir Mountains, the potential for mountaineering and outdoor adventure sports is vast. These activities can play a crucial role in promoting tourism, environmental awareness, and physical fitness within the country.\r\n\r\nThe AMF might organize training programs for climbers, conduct environmental conservation projects, and facilitate expeditions to some of the country\'s highest peaks. It may also work on mapping and developing climbing routes, advocating for the protection of natural areas, and engaging with local and international partners to boost the profile of Afghan mountaineering.\r\n\r\nHowever, it\'s important to note that the operating conditions for such organizations in Afghanistan can be challenging due to political instability, security concerns, and limited resources. These factors might influence the AMF\'s activities and its ability to achieve its goals.\r\n\r\nFor the most up-to-date information on the Afghanistan Mountaineering Federation, including its current projects, achievements, and how to get involved or support their work, it would be best to directly contact the organization or visit their official website or social media pages, if available.', '<p><span data-sheets-root=\"1\" data-sheets-value=\"{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;http://www.acmf.af/   acmf.af786@gmail.