(18, 'Kyrgyz Alpine Club (KAC)', 'Vladimir Komissarov', 'The Kyrgyz Alpine Club (KAC) is an organization dedicated to promoting alpinism and outdoor activities in Kyrgyzstan, a country known for its stunning mountainous landscapes, particularly the Tien Shan and Pamir mountain ranges. The club likely plays a significant role in fostering mountaineering, rock climbing, and related outdoor sports among both locals and international visitors. The activities and services provided by the KAC may include:\r\n\r\n1. Mountaineering Expeditions and Training**: Organizing climbs of various difficulties, including ascents of virgin peaks, and offering training programs for climbers of all skill levels.\r\n2. Conservation Efforts: Working to preserve the natural environment of Kyrgyzstan\'s mountains, advocating for sustainable practices among climbers and trekkers.\r\n3. Search and Rescue Operations: Providing or supporting search and rescue services for accidents in remote mountainous areas.\r\n4. Climbing Festivals and Competitions: Hosting events that bring together the mountaineering community, from local climbers to international participants.\r\n5. Route Development and Mapping: Developing new climbing routes and maintaining existing ones, including the creation and distribution of maps and guidebooks.\r\n6. Community Engagement: Engaging with local communities to support economic benefits from climbing and mountaineering tourism, and promoting outdoor education.\r\n\r\nThe Kyrgyz Alpine Club might also be involved in representing Kyrgyzstan in international climbing and mountaineering federations, advocating for the interests of climbers, and helping to elevate the profile of Kyrgyzstan as a premier destination for mountaineering.\r\n\r\nGiven the dynamic nature of outdoor organizations and the specifics of their operations which can change over time, for the latest information on the Kyrgyz Alpine Club, including upcoming events, membership details, and how to get invo