(20, 'Uzbekistan Mountaineering Federation (UMF)', 'Marco Maria Scolaris', 'The Uzbekistan Mountaineering Federation (UMF) is a sports organization in Uzbekistan dedicated to the development, promotion, and regulation of mountaineering and climbing sports within the country. The federation typically engages in activities such as organizing climbing expeditions, competitions, and training sessions for climbers of all levels, from beginners to experienced mountaineers. It also plays a crucial role in ensuring safety standards are maintained during mountaineering activities and expeditions in Uzbekistan\'s mountainous regions.\r\n\r\nUMF may also be involved in environmental conservation efforts to preserve the natural beauty and integrity of mountainous areas. This can include educating climbers and the public on sustainable and responsible climbing practices. Furthermore, the federation often represents Uzbekistan in international climbing and mountaineering communities, participating in global events and competitions.\r\n\r\nThe federation\'s goals usually include promoting physical health and wellbeing through climbing, fostering a community among climbers in Uzbekistan, and showcasing the country\'s mountainous landscapes as destinations for international climbers and tourists. By doing so, UMF contributes to the broader development of sports and tourism in Uzbekistan.', '<h2 class=\"uk-text-center uk-h2 uk-text-primary\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 1.1;\">TELEPHONE:&nbsp;+39 0113853995</h2><h2 class=\"uk-text-center uk-h2 uk-text-primary\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 1.1;\">FAX:&nbsp;+39 0114121773</h2><h2 class=\"uk-text-center uk-h2 uk-text-primary\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 1.1;\"><div class=\"uk-margin uk-text-center\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; margin-top: 20px !important;\"><p style=\"margin: 20px 0px;