(21, 'Mongolia Mountaineering Association (MMA)', 'Tulga Buya', 'The Mongolia Mountaineering Association (MMA) is an organization dedicated to promoting mountaineering, rock climbing, and related outdoor adventure sports in Mongolia. It serves as a national body that represents climbers and mountaineers in Mongolia, working to ensure safety standards, provide training, and foster a community for enthusiasts of these sports. While specific details about its foundation date and major achievements might vary, organizations like the MMA typically focus on:\r\n\r\n- Education and Training:Offering courses and certifications in mountaineering, rock climbing, ice climbing, and wilderness first aid to prepare individuals for safe adventures in the outdoors.\r\n\r\n- Conservation:Promoting and participating in efforts to preserve the natural environment in Mongolia\'s mountainous regions, ensuring that outdoor activities do not harm the ecosystem.\r\n\r\n- Community Building: Creating a platform for climbers and mountaineers to share experiences, plan expeditions, and collaborate on environmental initiatives.\r\n\r\n- Expedition Support and Regulation: Providing logistical support, information, and possibly permits for expeditions to Mongolia\'s mountains, including the Altai, Khangai, and Khentii ranges.\r\n\r\n- Competitions and Events: Organizing competitions and events to promote climbing sports, from local bouldering comps to national level mountaineering challenges.\r\n\r\nMongolia, with its vast and diverse landscapes, offers a unique backdrop for mountaineering and rock climbing. The country\'s high altitude areas, including the Tavan Bogd massif in the Altai Mountains, which houses Mongolia\'s highest peak, Mount Khuiten, are of particular interest to mountaineers and climbers from around the world.\r\n\r\nFor the most current information about the Mongolia Mountaineering Association, including membership details, upcoming events, and initiatives, visiting their official website or contacting them directly would provide the most accurate and up-to-date information.', '<span data-sheets-root=\"1\" data-sheets-value=\"{\"1\":2,\"2\":\"https://www.facebook.com/MountaineeringMongolAssociation/\"}\" data-sheets-userformat=\"{\"2\":1057665,\"3\":{\"1\":0},\"10\":0,\"11\":4,\"12\":0,\"16\":14,\"23\":1}\" data-sheets-hyperlink=\"https://www.facebook.com/MountaineeringMongolAssociation/\" style=\"text-decoration-line: underline; font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; color: rgb(5, 99, 193);\"><a class=\"in-cell-link\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/MountaineeringMongolAssociation/\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.facebook.com/MountaineeringMongolAssociation/</a></span>', '1709631826_29.png', NULL, 0, 17),
(22, 'Bangladesh Mountaineering Federation (BMF)', 'Kazi Wahidul Alam', 'The Bangladesh Mountaineering Federation (BMF) is a national organization in Bangladesh dedicated to the promotion and development of mountaineering and related activities in the country. Established to foster a culture of mountain sports, the BMF works to encourage and support the exploration and conservation of mountainous regions both within Bangladesh and internationally. The organization\'s activities typically include organizing expeditions, mountaineering training and courses, environmental conservation initiatives, and promoting safety standards within the mountaineering community.\r\n\r\nThe BMF serves as a platform for enthusiasts, climbers, and adventurers to come together to share their experiences, learn new skills, and participate in expeditions. It often collaborates with national and international mountaineering bodies to enhance the capabilities of Bangladeshi mountaineers and to represent Bangladesh in the global mountaineering community. The federation is also involved in youth development programs, aiming to inspire the next generation of mountaineers through education and hands-on experiences in the outdoors.\r\n\r\nBy advocating for the preservation of natural environments and promoting sustainable practices, the BMF contributes to the broader conversation on environmental stewardship. It plays a crucial role in raising awareness about the challenges facing mountain ecosystems and communities, leveraging the popularity of mountaineering to foster a deeper connection between people and the natural world.\r\n\r\nWhile specific details about its founding date, leadership, and membership can vary over time, the overarching goal of the Bangladesh Mountaineering Federation remains consistent: to nurture a love for the mountains among Bangladeshis and to equip them with the skills and knowledge necessary for safe and responsible mountaineering.', '<p>008801816603111</p><p>       