(29, 'Union of Asian Alpine Associations (UAAA)', 'No Specific Name', '<span data-sheets-root=\"1\" data-sheets-value=\"{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;The Union of Asian Alpine Associations (UAAA) is a collective organization that encompasses various national alpine associations throughout Asia. Its primary goal is to promote mountaineering and climbing activities in the Asian continent. The organization focuses on fostering cooperation and collaboration among member countries, sharing knowledge and information related to mountaineering, and working on environmental conservation efforts in mountainous areas.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe UAAA plays a crucial role in organizing events, expeditions, and training programs to enhance safety standards and mountaineering skills among climbers in Asia. It also serves as a platform for discussing and addressing issues related to mountain conservation, access rights, and sustainable climbing practices.\\r\\n\\r\\nMember associations of the UAAA come from a wide range of countries, reflecting the geographical diversity and cultural richness of Asia. Through its activities, the UAAA aims to strengthen the mountaineering community in Asia and contribute to the global climbing and outdoor adventure scene.\\r\\n\\r\\nWhile specific details about its formation date, founding members, and the full list of current member associations might require further research, the UAAA is recognized for its efforts in promoting mountaineering and environmental stewardship across the Asian continent.&quot;}\" data-sheets-userformat=\"{&quot;2&quot;:9089,&quot;3&quot;:{&quot;1&quot;:0},&quot;10&quot;:0,&quot;11&quot;:4,&quot;12&quot;:0,&quot;16&quot;:14}\" style=\"\">The Union of Asian Alpine Associations (UAAA) is a collective organization that encompasses various national alpine associations throughout Asia. Its primary goal is to promote mountaineering and climbing activities in the Asian continent. The organization focuses on fostering cooperation and collaboration among member countries, sharing knowledge and information related to mountaineering, and working on environmental conservation efforts in mountainous areas.<br><br>The UAAA plays a crucial role in organizing events, expeditions, and training programs to enhance safety standards and mountaineering skills among climbers in Asia. It also serves as a platform for discussing and addressing issues related to mountain conservation, access rights, and sustainable climbing practices.<br><br>Member associations of the UAAA come from a wide range of countries, reflecting the geographical diversity and cultural richness of Asia. Through its activities, the UAAA aims to strengthen the mountaineering community in Asia and contribute to the global climbing and outdoor adventure scene.<br><br>While specific details about its formation date, founding members, and the full list of current member associations might require further research, the UAAA is recognized for its efforts in promoting mountaineering and environmental stewardship across the Asian continent.</span>', '<p><span data-sheets-root=\"1\" data-sheets-value=\"{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;UAAA office, 6F, Kingkong bldg., 86, Chungdamdong, Kangnamgu, Seoul, Korea |Tel. 822 558 3331 |Fax. 822 501 8848 |E-mail. info@theuaaa.org&quot;}\" data-sheets-userformat=\"{&quot;2&quot;:9089,&quot;3&quot;:{&quot;1&quot;:0},&quot;10&quot;:0,&quot;11&quot;:4,&quot;12&quot;:0,&quot;16&quot;:14}\" style=\"\">UAAA office, 6F, Kingkong bldg., 86, Chungdamdong, Kangnamgu, Seoul, Korea </span></p><p><span data-sheets-root=\"1\" data-sheets-value=\"{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;UAAA office, 6F, Kingkong bldg., 86, Chungdamdong, Kangnamgu, Seoul, Korea |Tel. 822 558 3331 |Fax. 822 501 8848 |E-mail. info@theuaaa.org&quot;}\" data-sheets-userformat=\"{&quot;2&quot;:9089,&quot;3&quot;:{&quot;1&quot;:0},&quot;10&quot;:0,&quot;11&quot;:4,&quot;12&quot;:0,&quot;16&quot;:14}\" style=\"\">Tel. 822 558 3331 Fax. 822 501 884