(28, 'Dzungarian Alatau', '1.jpg', 'The Dzungarian Alatau is a mountain range located in Central Asia, specifically in the border region between Kazakhstan, China, and Kyrgyzstan. Here\'s a description of the Dzungarian Alatau: \r\n\r\n1. Location: The Dzungarian Alatau stretches across the southeastern part of Kazakhstan, extending into Xinjiang Province in western China and southern regions of Kyrgyzstan. It is part of the larger Tian Shan mountain system. \r\n\r\n2. Geography: The range is characterized by rugged, rocky terrain with numerous peaks, valleys, and gorges. It is predominantly composed of sedimentary and metamorphic rock formations. \r\n\r\n3. Elevation: The highest peak in the Dzungarian Alatau is Khan Tengri, which stands at approximately 7,010 meters (22,999 feet) above sea level. Other notable peaks include Khan Tengri\'s sub-peaks, as well as peaks such as Victory Peak (also known as Jengish Chokusu), which is the highest peak in Kyrgyzstan. \r\n\r\n4. Climate: The climate in the Dzungarian Alatau varies depending on altitude and location. Generally, the region experiences a continental climate with cold winters and relatively warm summers. Precipitation levels are typically lower in the rain shadow of the mountains. \r\n5. Flora and Fauna: The Dzungarian Alatau supports a diverse range of plant and animal species adapted to mountainous environments. Vegetation varies from alpine meadows and coniferous forests at lower elevations to barren, rocky slopes at higher altitudes. Wildlife includes species such as ibex, snow leopards, lynx, and various bird species. \r\n\r\n6. Cultural Significance: The region has been historically inhabited by various nomadic and semi-nomadic tribes, including Kazakhs, Kyrgyz, and ethnic groups of Xinjiang. These communities have traditionally engaged in pastoralism, herding livestock such as sheep, goats, and horses across the mountainous terrain. \r\n\r\n7. Recreation: The Dzungarian Alatau offers opportunities for outdoor activities such as trekking, mountaineering, and camping. The region\'s stunning natural beauty attracts adventurers and nature enthusiasts from around the world. \r\n\r\nOverall, the Dzungarian Alatau is a majestic mountain range with rich biodiversity and cultural heritage, making it a significant natural and recreational asset in Central Asia.', 'The history of the Dzungarian Alatau, like much of Central Asia, is rich and complex, shaped by the movements of various nomadic tribes, empires, and geopolitical shifts over millennia. Here\'s an overview: \r\n\r\n1. Nomadic Tribes**: The region surrounding the Dzungarian Alatau has been inhabited by nomadic peoples for thousands of years. Tribes such as the Scythians, Saka, and later the Turkic-speaking tribes, including the Kazakhs and Kyrgyz, roamed these lands, practicing pastoralism and engaging in trade along the Silk Road. \r\n\r\n2. Mongol Empire**: In the 13th century, the Mongol Empire, under the leadership of Genghis Khan and his successors, expanded across much of Asia, including parts of Central Asia encompassing the Dzungarian Alatau. The region became integrated into the vast Mongol-controlled territories, facilitating trade and cultural exchange. \r\n\r\n3. Turkic Khanates: Following the decline of the Mongol Empire, various Turkic Khanates emerged in Central Asia, including the Kazakh Khanate and the Khanate of Kokand. These Khanates vied for control over the region, leading to periods of conflict and alliances. \r\n\r\n4. Russian Expansion: In the 18th and 19th centuries, the Russian Empire began expanding into Central Asia, seeking to consolidate its control over the region and secure trade routes to China. This expansion gradually brought the lands surrounding the Dzungarian Alatau under Russian influence. \r\n\r\n5. Soviet Era: With the Russian Revolution of 1917, Central Asia came under Bolshevik control, and the Soviet Union was established. The Dzungarian Alatau, along with the rest of Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan, and Xinjiang, became part of the Soviet Union. During this period, the Soviet government implemented policies aimed at modernizing the region, including collectivization of agriculture and industrial development. \r\n\r\n6. Modern Era: With the collapse of the Soviet Union in 1991, the countries of Central Asia gained independence. Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan, and China (Xinjiang) now govern the territories encompassing the Dzungarian Alatau. These countries have focused on developing their economies, preserving cultural heritage, and managing natural resources in the region. \r\n\r\nThroughout its history, the Dzungarian Alatau has been a crossroads of cultures, a gateway for trade and migration, and a battleground for competing empires. Today, it remains an integral part of the cultural and geographical landscape of Central Asia.', 'Surviving in the Dzungarian Alatau Range, a high and wild mountainous area, requires basic survival skills and an understanding of the mountain environment: \r\n\r\n1. Mountaineering and trekking skills: Moving through high mountainous areas and hills requires mountaineering and trekking skills. Being prepared to deal with harsh weather conditions and rugged terrain is crucial. \r\n\r\n2. Survival skills in nature: Knowing how to search for and gather food from nature such as fruits, nuts, herbs, or even hunting or fishing if necessary. Knowledge of edible plant and animal species and how to identify them is essential. \r\n\r\n3. Camp building and self-protection skills: Knowing how to build temporary shelters or tents using natural materials such as grass, animal fur, and rocks. Also, understanding how to protect oneself from harsh weather and dangerous animals or insects. \r\n\r\n4. Orientation skills and tool usage: Knowing how to orient oneself using maps, sun position, tracks, and natural signs. Also, having skills in using basic tools like knives, ropes, and axes for self-protection and shelter building. \r\n\r\n5. Communication and teamwork skills: In the wilderness environment, communication and teamwork are crucial for sharing knowledge, experience, and resources. Collaborating with others can enhance survival and safety. \r\n\r\n6. Cultural and local knowledge: Understanding the culture and lifestyle of local people can help create a harmonious and safer living environment. \r\n\r\nIn summary, surviving in the Dzungarian Alatau Range requires a combination of natural skills, survival skills, teamwork, as well as an understanding of the environment and local culture.', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d57287.841757368646!2d79.9687084669527!3d44.996659114660694!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x4281b26484e7e919%3A0x4c076b87d836029!2sDzungarian%20Alatau!5e0!3m2!1svi!2s!4v1708868974837!5m2!1svi!2s\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe>', 'Located in the east of Kazakhstan, near the border with China.', 'When mountain climbing in the Dzungarian Alatau Range, choosing a place to stay requires careful consideration and the ability to assess the safety of the surrounding environment. Here are some tips for choosing a place to stay when mountain climbing in this area: \r\n\r\n1. Terrain: Choose a location on flat and stable terrain, away from steep cliffs, crevices, or steep slopes prone to rockslides. \r\n\r\n2. Water source: Choose a location near a clean water source that is easily accessible to ensure a supply of drinking water and water for cooking. \r\n\r\n3. Protection from wind and bad weather: Choose a location within the protection of high hills or mountain peaks to minimize the impact of strong winds and bad weather. \r\n\r\n4. Check for flood risk: Avoid choosing a location near rivers or streams if there is a risk of flooding, and always check the surrounding area to ensure safety. \r\n\r\n5. Assess earthquake and landslide risk: Avoid choosing a location under steep cliffs, and always select a place on hard and stable ground. \r\n\r\n6. Consider proximity to areas with earthquake and landslide risk: Always research the earthquake and landslide risks in the area, and avoid choosing a location too close to areas with high risk. \r\n\r\n7. Protect the environment: Choose a location that does not impact the natural environment and ensures you do not cut or damage local flora and fauna. \r\n\r\nRemember to always adhere to safety rules when choosing a place to stay and continuously evaluate and adjust your accommodation to ensure safety and comfort when mountain climbing in the Dzungarian Alatau Range.', 'The Dzungarian Alatau Range can present significant challenges and dangers for mountaineers or explorers venturing into this area. Below are some common hazards that people need to face when accessing this region: \r\n\r\n1. Extreme Weather: This mountain range can experience extremely harsh weather conditions, including storms, heavy snowfall, strong winds, and even natural disasters such as landslides or floods. These conditions can pose dangers to the health and lives of mountaineers. \r\n\r\n2. Diverse and Hazardous Terrain: Dzungarian Alatau features diverse terrain, including crevasses, steep cliffs, high hills, and dangerous rivers and streams. This can pose risks to mountaineers, especially when navigating through unsafe areas. \r\n\r\n3. Risk of Landslides and Earthquakes: Mountainous areas are prone to landslides and earthquakes, especially after rainfall or in extreme weather conditions. These phenomena can pose serious dangers to mountaineers. \r\n\r\n4. Lack of Water and Food: In some areas, water sources can be very scarce, especially during dry seasons or at higher altitudes. This can lead to risks of dehydration and starvation for mountaineers, especially if they are not adequately prepared beforehand. \r\n\r\n5. Risk of Accidents and Injuries: Activities such as mountain climbing, long-distance hiking, and exploration can lead to risks of accidents and injuries, including slips, falls, or injuries during movement. \r\n\r\nTherefore, thorough preparation, knowledge of the environment and weather conditions, along with having safety equipment and an experienced guide team can help minimize risks and increase survival chances when accessing the Dzungarian Alatau Range.', 0),
(29, 'Aravalli', '1.jpg', 'The Aravalli Range is a prominent mountain range in Northwestern India, running approximately 692 km in a southwest direction across the states of Gujarat, Rajasthan, Haryana, and ending in Delhi. Here\'s a description of the Aravalli Range: \r\n\r\n1. Location: The Aravalli Range stretches from the southwestern tip of Gujarat near the Gulf of Cambay to the northeast part of Rajasthan near the Yamuna River. \r\n\r\n2. Geography: It forms a natural boundary between the arid Thar Desert to the northwest and the fertile plains of the Indo-Gangetic plain to the southeast. The range is characterized by low hills, rocky outcrops, and isolated plateaus. \r\n\r\n3. Highest Peaks: Though not very high compared to other mountain ranges, the highest peak in the Aravalli Range is Guru Shikhar, which rises to an elevation of 1,722 meters (5,650 feet) above sea level. Mount Abu, the only hill station in Rajasthan, is located in the southern part of this range. \r\n\r\n4. Geological Significance: The Aravalli Range is one of the oldest fold mountain ranges in the world, dating back to the Precambrian era. Its formation is attributed to the collision of the Indian Plate with the Eurasian Plate. \r\n\r\n5. Biodiversity**: Despite its semi-arid climate, the Aravalli Range supports a rich biodiversity. It is home to various species of flora and fauna, including several endangered species such as leopards, Indian sloth bears, and Indian pangolins. \r\n\r\n6. Human History**: The Aravalli Range has a long history of human habitation, with evidence of ancient settlements dating back to the Stone Age. It has been inhabited by various indigenous communities and has served as a natural barrier and a source of mineral wealth for civilizations throughout history. \r\n\r\n7. Environmental Concerns: The Aravalli Range faces environmental challenges such as deforestation, mining activities, and urbanization, which pose threats to its fragile ecosystem and biodiversity. \r\n\r\n8. Tourism and Recreation: The scenic beauty of the Aravalli Range, along with its historical and cultural significance, attracts tourists and adventure enthusiasts. Visitors can explore national parks, wildlife sanctuaries, and historic sites scattered throughout the region. \r\n\r\nOverall, the Aravalli Range is not only a geographical feature but also a cultural and ecological treasure that plays a crucial role in shaping the landscape and livelihoods of the regions it traverses.', 'The Aravalli Range has a rich and diverse history that spans thousands of years. Here\'s an overview of its historical significance: \r\n\r\n1. Early Settlements: The Aravalli Range has been inhabited by humans since ancient times. Archaeological evidence suggests that Stone Age communities lived in the region, utilizing its natural resources for sustenance. \r\n\r\n2. Ancient Civilizations: The Aravalli Range has played a significant role in the development of ancient Indian civilizations. It served as a natural barrier, protecting settlements from invasions and fostering the growth of indigenous cultures. \r\n\r\n3. Mining and Metallurgy: One of the most notable aspects of the Aravalli\'s history is its rich mineral deposits. The range has been a major source of minerals such as copper, zinc, lead, and marble for centuries. Ancient civilizations like the Indus Valley Civilization and later kingdoms utilized these resources for trade and craftsmanship. \r\n\r\n4. Historical Trade Routes: The Aravalli Range was situated along important trade routes that connected the Indian subcontinent with Central Asia and beyond. These routes facilitated the exchange of goods, ideas, and cultures, contributing to the region\'s prosperity and cultural diversity. \r\n\r\n5. Medieval Kingdoms: During the medieval period, various kingdoms and dynasties ruled over parts of the Aravalli region. Rajput kingdoms such as Mewar, Marwar, and Amber established their capitals in the vicinity of the range, constructing forts, palaces, and temples that still stand as architectural marvels today. \r\n\r\n6. Colonial Era: With the advent of colonialism, the Aravalli Range came under the control of various European powers, including the British East India Company. The British exploited the region\'s mineral wealth and established administrative centers, leaving a lasting impact on its landscape and society. \r\n\r\n7. Independence Movement: The Aravalli region, like the rest of India, played a significant role in the struggle for independence against British rule. It was a hotbed of nationalist activities, with many freedom fighters hailing from the area and participating in various movements and campaigns. \r\n\r\n8. Modern Development: In the post-independence era, the Aravalli Range has witnessed rapid urbanization, industrialization, and infrastructural development. However, these processes have also led to environmental degradation, deforestation, and the depletion of natural resources, raising concerns about sustainable development and conservation. \r\n\r\nOverall, the history of the Aravalli Range reflects the intertwined narratives of human civilization, natural resource utilization, and socio-political dynamics, making it a fascinating subject of study for historians, archaeologists, and environmentalists alike.', 'When mountaineering in the Aravalli Range or any other mountain range, there are several important survival skills you need to ensure safety and success in your mountain climbing expedition. Here are some crucial skills when mountaineering in the Aravalli Range: \r\n\r\n1. Mountain and Environmental Knowledge: Understanding the terrain, weather, and natural conditions of the Aravalli Range is crucial. This includes knowing how to read maps and use navigation equipment. \r\n\r\n2. Mountaineering Skills: Knowing how to climb mountains safely and efficiently is extremely important. This includes using proper climbing techniques, such as footwork, handholds, and harnesses. \r\n\r\n3. Mountain Safety: Ensure you always carry full safety equipment such as helmets, harnesses, and a rescue kit. Always adhere to safety rules when mountaineering, including maintaining a safe distance, never climbing alone, and always informing someone of your plans. \r\n\r\n4. Navigation and Tracking Skills: Knowing how to navigate and track is crucial when mountaineering. There may be trails that are not clearly marked, so this skill will help you avoid getting lost and find your way back. \r\n\r\n5. Basic First Aid Knowledge: Having knowledge of how to handle emergency situations and administer simple first aid is crucial when mountaineering. This includes knowing how to clean and bandage wounds, as well as how to call for rescue when necessary. \r\n\r\n6. Basic Survival Skills: Carrying enough water and food, protecting yourself from the impact of harsh weather, and knowing how to handle emergency situations such as getting lost are important survival skills when mountaineering. \r\n\r\nRemember that mountaineering in the Aravalli Range or any other mountain range offers great experiences, but ensuring safety is always the most important thing.', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3676328.066887905!2d72.02134242359901!3d25.864075009243354!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x39681ddaac30be25%3A0x51bcfe8c70434f74!2zRMOjeSBuw7ppIEFyYXZhbGxp!5e0!3m2!1svi!2s!4v1708869225350!5m2!1svi!2s\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe>', 'Found in the west of India, running through the state of Rajasthan.', 'When mountain climbing in the Aravalli Range, choosing accommodation depends on various factors such as the difficulty of the climb, the expected duration of the trip, and specific destinations you want to explore. Here are some popular options for accommodation when mountain climbing in the Aravalli Range: \r\n\r\n1. Nearby Towns: There are several towns and areas near the Aravalli Range that you can use as a starting point or lodging. Towns such as Mount Abu, Udaipur, and Ajmer provide accommodation, restaurants, and other amenities for travelers. \r\n\r\n2. Outdoor Campsites: If you want a closer experience with nature, you may consider camping outdoors in permitted camping areas. However, be sure to adhere to camping regulations and environmental protection. \r\n\r\n3. Guesthouses and Homestays: In some areas near the Aravalli Range, you can find guesthouses, homestays, or small hotels providing accommodation for tourists. This can be a comfortable and convenient option after a tiring day of mountain climbing. \r\n\r\n4. Farmstays and Rural Homestays: If you want to experience rural life and interact with the local community, staying at farmstays or rural homestays near the Aravalli Range can be a good option. \r\n\r\n5. Resorts: Some luxury resorts and villa resorts may be located in areas near the Aravalli Range, offering comfortable spaces and luxurious amenities for travelers. \r\n\r\nBefore deciding on accommodation when mountain climbing in the Aravalli Range, consider factors such as budget, amenities, and the purpose of your trip to choose the most suitable option. Additionally, make sure you always adhere to safety rules and environmental protection when lodging and mountain climbing.', 'Aravalli, like any other mountain range, can pose several dangers and challenges that make mountain climbing hazardous. Here are some hazardous factors that mountain climbers may face when exploring the Aravalli Range: \r\n\r\nHarsh Weather: The weather in the Aravalli Range can be unpredictable and harsh, especially during the summer and monsoon seasons. Storms, floods, or heavy rainfall can pose dangers to mountain climbers. \r\n\r\nDiverse Terrain: The Aravalli Range features diverse terrain, from high mountain peaks to deep valleys. Navigating through these terrains may require high-level mountaineering and navigation skills. \r\n\r\nRisk of Getting Lost: With the complex and dense forested terrain, the risk of getting lost is a concern. Getting lost in the Aravalli Range can lead to risks and difficulties in finding the way back to the starting point. \r\n\r\nWildlife Hazards: The Aravalli Range is home to various wild animals, including lions, leopards, and tigers. While attacks from these animals are not common, caution and knowing how to deal with encounters are necessary. \r\n\r\nAccidents and Injuries: Risks of accidents such as slips, falls, or getting trapped can occur during mountain climbing. Ensuring safety and having basic first aid skills are crucial. \r\n\r\nWildfires: During the summer, the risk of wildfires and forest fires increases in the Aravalli Range. This can pose dangers and affect the health of mountain climbers. \r\n\r\nTo minimize risks and ensure safety when mountain climbing in the Aravalli Range, always practice safety measures such as carrying full protective gear, following mountaineering rules, and considering weather and environmental conditions before embarking on the journey.', 0),
(30, 'Arakan', '1.jpg', 'The Arakan Range, with its towering peaks and year-round mist, creates a mystical landscape. The range runs along the border between Myanmar and Bangladesh, forming a natural barrier between the two countries. Its slopes are covered with tropical rainforests, home to many unique and biologically diverse wildlife species, as well as being a refuge for ethnic minorities with their own customs and traditions', 'The history of the Arakan Range is intertwined with the formation and development of cultures in the region. It has witnessed historical battles, served as a sanctuary for monks and ascetics, and inspired numerous legends and folk stories. Ancient temples and historical relics scattered across valleys and mountainsides testify to a glorious past.', 'To survive in the harsh environment of the Arakan Range, one needs skills in finding food and water, building shelters, and navigating through the forest. Additionally, understanding the wildlife and knowing how to avoid or deal with them is extremely important.', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d14872.146343271852!2d93.93970026432497!3d21.270019333147488!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x30b410f6f3c3d86d%3A0x1681f947e965badf!2zRMOjeSBuw7ppIEFyYWthbg!5e0!3m2!1svi!2s!4v1708946532999!5m2!1svi!2s\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe>', 'Situated in the west of Myanmar.', 'Shelters can be found in natural caves, under dense canopies, or by building huts from natural materials. The friendly local communities can also provide necessary support and guidance to visitors.', 'The Arakan Range harbors many dangers, including wild animals such as leopards and venomous snakes, as well as natural hazards like floods and landslides. Security issues due to regional conflicts are also a significant concern. \r\n\r\nThe Arakan Range is not only a part of the natural landscape but also a symbol of strength, resilience, and beauty unmatched anywhere else in the world. The journey to explore this range is a true adventure, a challenging experience that also rewards with discoveries about nature and oneself.', 0),
(31, 'Altay', '1.jpg', 'The Altay Mountains are a complex mountain system featuring towering peaks, deep valleys, glaciers, and crystal-clear lakes. It is a meeting point for a variety of ecosystems, from cold taiga forests to vast steppes and arid deserts. The Altay is not only an ideal destination for nature lovers and outdoor activities but also a crucial site for scientific research and biodiversity conservation.', 'The history of the Altay Mountains is intertwined with various cultures and ethnic groups. It has been the home of nomadic tribes since ancient times, the source of numerous legends, and a vital point in ancient trade routes. Archaeological discoveries have revealed many precious historical relics, including kurgans (burial mounds) and petroglyphs (rock carvings), testifying to a rich and diverse past.', 'Surviving in the Altay Mountains requires orientation skills, the ability to find water and food, and the skill to build shelters. Due to the extreme weather conditions and harsh terrain, survival skills also include knowing how to stay warm and deal with natural risks.', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d10470.222574481799!2d88.98970027816625!3d49.00001311917424!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x42b46aff10e71ecf%3A0x35ef4923e8cabcea!2zRMOjeSBuw7ppIEFsdGF5!5e0!3m2!1svi!2s!4v1708946736494!5m2!1svi!2s\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe>', 'Located in the west of Mongolia, near the borders with Russia and China.', 'Shelters in the Altay Mountains include natural caves, huts made from local materials, or accommodations built by local communities or conservation organizations.', 'Dangers in the Altay Mountains include harsh weather, treacherous terrain, wildlife such as bears and wolves, as well as risks from activities like mountain climbing and hiking. Isolation can increase risks, requiring a high level of preparation and knowledge on handling emergency situations.', 0),
(32, 'Sayan', '1.jpg', 'The Sayan Mountains form part of the natural boundary between southern Siberia and the northern regions of Mongolia. With towering peaks, deep and broad valleys, along with glacier systems and crystal-clear lakes, the Sayan Mountains are not just scenic but also a habitat for rich biodiversity, including many endemic flora and fauna species.', 'The Sayan Mountains have a long and rich history, once inhabited by nomadic tribes. They are an important part of the history and culture of the indigenous peoples, especially the Tuvans, with many legends and traditions associated with these mountains.', 'Surviving in the Sayan Mountains requires skills in finding water, food, building shelters, and orienteering in the wilderness. Due to extreme weather conditions and challenging terrain, survival skills also include knowing how to stay warm and cope with natural challenges', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d26649568.605196673!2d27.191892574110984!3d35.37745066448461!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x5d248057b355ccaf%3A0xbd2bfa17918f8e8!2zRMOjeSBuw7ppIFNheWFu!5e0!3m2!1svi!2s!4v1708946954671!5m2!1svi!2s\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe>', 'Found in the southern part of Siberia, Russia.', 'Shelter can be found in natural caves, huts made from local materials, or accommodations built by local communities for visitors and explorers.', 'Dangers in the Sayan Mountains include harsh weather, treacherous terrain, wildlife such as wolves and bears, as well as risks from activities like mountain climbing and hiking. Isolation and harsh conditions require thorough preparation and knowledge on handling emergency situations. \r\n\r\nThe Sayan Mountains are not just a challenge for those seeking adventure and natural exploration but also a source of inspiration for the beauty and power of nature.', 0),
(33, 'Verkhoyansk Range', '1.jpg', 'The Verkhoyansk Range is one of the coldest and most inhospitable regions on Earth, with average elevations ranging from 1,800 to 2,000 meters (5,900 to 6,600 feet). This area is covered in snow year-round and can experience winter temperatures dropping to -67.8?C (-90?F). The terrain comprises a series of high mountains, deep valleys, and ice rivers.', 'The Verkhoyansk Range has been home to indigenous peoples such as the Evenks and Yakuts for thousands of years. In the 19th century, it became a significant center for gold and other precious metal mining after the first gold deposits were discovered in Yakutsk in 1830.', 'Surviving in the Verkhoyansk Range requires careful preparation and strong survival skills, including building sturdy shelters, using snow transportation, and knowing how to find food from the natural environment. It also involves dealing with risks such as landslides and avalanches', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d6235.782897330218!2d128.98970029227186!3d67.00000765123147!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x5b9159ec09823ab5%3A0xa9fa16c8c460bd0c!2sVerkhoyansk%20Range!5e0!3m2!1svi!2s!4v1708948298439!5m2!1svi!2s\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe>', 'Verkhoyansk Range is situated in northeastern Russia, running parallel to the Sakha region, near the Lena River, and at a distance from the East Siberian Sea.', 'The Verkhoyansk Range offers many natural shelters such as caves, dense forests, and various land entrances, but caution must be taken with risks of landslides and avalanches, as well as thorough preparation to ensure safety when using these places.', 'Dangers in the Verkhoyansk Range include extreme cold temperatures, avalanches, the risk of losing landmarks in harsh weather conditions, and the danger from ice rivers in summer when water rises from melted snow.', 0),
(34, 'Jabal al-Lawz', '1.jpg', 'Jabal al-Lawz, also known as \"Mountain of Almonds,\" is a noteworthy landmark in Saudi Arabia, often surrounded by stories and legends.Jabal al-Lawz is part of the Sarawat Mountain range, located in northwest Saudi Arabia, near the border with Jordan. The mountain stands approximately 2,580 meters (8,465 feet) above sea level, notable for its snow-capped peak in winter, which is quite rare for a desert country like Saudi Arabia. The area also features diverse terrain with valleys, plateaus, and water stream systems.', 'Jabal al-Lawz holds a special place in traditions and myths, with some sources suggesting it could be the actual location of Mount Sinai, where Moses received the Ten Commandments. However, this remains a topic of much debate and has not been widely accepted by mainstream science.', 'Surviving in Jabal al-Lawz requires basic hiking and camping skills, orienteering abilities, and the crucial skill of finding water due to the arid nature of the region. Additionally, preparing appropriate clothing to cope with cold temperatures at night and sudden weather changes is necessary.', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d158489.73212973823!2d35.27919339455658!3d28.624924853407684!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x15abab47c58d444b%3A0x2079827a3ea5ea2c!2sJabal%20al-Lawz!5e0!3m2!1svi!2s!4v1708947547940!5m2!1svi!2s\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe>', 'Situated in the northwest of Saudi Arabia.', 'The surrounding area of Jabal al-Lawz can provide temporary shelter in natural caves or by setting up camp with camping gear. However, due to the area\'s underdeveloped tourism infrastructure, accommodation options may be limited.', 'The main dangers at Jabal al-Lawz include rocky and treacherous terrain, water scarcity, and harsh weather conditions, especially in winter when temperatures can drop very low. Additionally, traversing desert areas also poses health risks due to high temperatures and lack of water. \r\n\r\nJabal al-Lawz is not only an important part of the natural landscape and culture of Saudi Arabia but also an appealing destination for those who love exploration, history, and outdoor adventures.', 0),
(35, 'Sikhote-Alin', '1.jpg', 'The Sikhote-Alin mountain range is a long and majestic range located in the Far East of Russia, renowned for its stunning natural landscapes, rich biodiversity, and abundant history.Sikhote-Alin stretches across Russia\'s Far East, distinguished by its vast primeval forests, high biodiversity, and as a habitat for rare species such as the Siberian tiger. This mountain range is also part of a world biosphere reserve, highlighting its importance for environmental conservation and scientific research.', 'The history of the Sikhote-Alin is closely linked with the indigenous peoples and cultures of the Russian Far East. The range is also famous for the Sikhote-Alin meteorite event in 1947, one of the largest and most well-documented meteorite events in history.', 'Surviving in the Sikhote-Alin mountains requires orienteering skills, the ability to find food and water, as well as shelter-building skills. Given the area\'s diverse wildlife and harsh weather conditions, thorough preparation and understanding of the environment are crucial.', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d10777.129354785544!2d138.00435347716288!3d47.52336597911127!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x5ee3c066a7e1689b%3A0xb6bf40ef25b4ce95!2sSikhote-Alin!5e0!3m2!1svi!2s!4v1708947932849!5m2!1svi!2s\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe>', 'Found in the east of Russia, near the Sea of Japan.', 'The area surrounding the Sikhote-Alin range offers numerous natural shelters such as caves, dense forests, and some designated camping areas. However, due to strict environmental protections, finding shelter must comply with conservation regulations.', 'The main dangers in the Sikhote-Alin range include wildlife, especially the Siberian tiger, harsh weather, and treacherous terrain. Additionally, navigating through primeval forests requires utmost caution to avoid getting lost or encountering other risks from the environment. \r\n\r\nThe Sikhote-Alin mountain range is not only a valuable natural heritage but also a challenge and opportunity for those passionate about natural exploration, environmental conservation, and outdoor adventure.', 0),
(36, 'Sahand', '1.jpg', 'The Sahand mountain range is renowned for its majestic mountain landscape and unique natural beauty. With its snow-capped peaks, this range creates a stunning panorama, especially in winter. It is also home to numerous rivers, streams, and lakes, contributing to the richness of the natural environment.', 'The Sahand mountain range has a diverse and rich history, documented in many literary works and historical records of Iran. In Iranian folklore, Sahand is often considered a sacred place and is featured in many myths and legends.', 'Living in the Sahand mountain range requires strong survival skills and adaptability. Harsh weather conditions and rugged terrain demand the ability to build sturdy shelters, gather food from nature, and handle emergencies such as severe weather and landslide risks.', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d12622.287643618858!2d46.489785871214124!3d37.72972507302674!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x401a4b1441ac264b%3A0x58326033a67b8356!2sSahand!5e0!3m2!1svi!2s!4v1708949095469!5m2!1svi!2s\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe>', 'Located near the city of Tabriz, Iran.', 'The Sahand mountain range offers many natural shelters, including caves, rock faces, and crevices in the terrain, but caution must be taken with landslide risks and hazards from harsh weather conditions.', 'Hazards in the Sahand mountain range include the risk of extreme cold, harsh climates, rugged terrain, landslide, and avalanche risks, especially in winter and during the rainy season. Thorough preparation and survival skills are necessary to face these challenges when exploring this mountain range.', 0),
(37, 'Kanchenjunga', '1.jpg', 'Mount Kanchenjunga is one of the highest mountains in the world, located in the Himalayas, northeast of Nepal and north of the Indian state of Sikkim. With an elevation of 8,586 meters (28,169 feet), it is the third-highest mountain in the world. Kanchenjunga has a large conical shape, with its summit covered in snow and ice year-round, creating a majestic and mystical landscape.', 'Kanchenjunga has been known since the 19th century but was not named until 1852. The mountain was unconquered until 1955 when a British-Nepalese expedition reached its summit. It was officially climbed for the first time in 1955 by a British expedition.', 'Climbing Mount Kanchenjunga requires professional mountaineering skills, exceptional patience, and high endurance. Thorough preparation and knowledge of mountaineering techniques and safety are essential.', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d14129.913887790712!2d88.13723526652164!3d27.70250956710596!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x39e6584a17958853%3A0x716f448087dc6d4c!2sKanchenjunga!5e0!3m2!1svi!2s!4v1708949255246!5m2!1svi!2s\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe>', 'Positioned on the border between Nepal and India, near Sikkim, India.', 'The area around Mount Kanchenjunga is home to many rare species of animals and is one of the most pristine and beautiful regions in the world. Travelers often have the opportunity to encounter these species while participating in trekking expeditions through the area.', 'Hazards when climbing Mount Kanchenjunga include risks from extreme weather, altitude, snow and ice avalanches, landslide risks, and medical hazards. Thorough preparation and contingency planning are necessary before embarking on this mountain expedition. \r\n\r\nThese details provide an overview of Mount Kanchenjunga, one of the famous and enticing destinations for mountain climbers and nature enthusiasts.', 0),
(38, 'Nanda Devi', '1.jpg', 'Nanda Devi is a mountain in the Himalayas, located in the state of Uttarakhand, India. With an approximate height of 7,816 meters (25,643 feet), it is the second-highest mountain in India after Kangchenjunga. Nanda Devi is considered one of the most beautiful and majestic mountains in the world, with a conical shape and mystical beauty.', 'Nanda Devi has been known since ancient times in the culture and religion of India. It is considered a sacred mountain and worshipped by many local people. In modern history, it has attracted the attention of mountaineers and explorers from around the world.', 'Climbing Mount Nanda Devi requires professional mountaineering skills and ample experience with the special mountain conditions in the Himalayas. Patience, endurance, and knowledge of mountain safety are essential.', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d13745.15811423695!2d79.9612761676973!3d30.541122975657544!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x39a7a9b1b9aed97b%3A0xc6505ec96e4dc4bb!2sNanda%20Devi!5e0!3m2!1svi!2s!4v1708949876289!5m2!1svi!2s\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe>', 'Found in the state of Uttarakhand, India.', 'Nanda Devi and the surrounding area are home to many rare species of animals and plants. This area also attracts numerous mountaineers and tourists seeking to explore and enjoy the pristine beauty of the Himalayas.', 'Climbing Mount Nanda Devi faces not only risks from harsh weather and complex terrain of the Himalayas but also unique challenges such as dangers from snow and ice, landslides, and medical hazards. Thorough preparation and safety planning are extremely important when embarking on mountain expeditions here.', 0),
(39, 'Paektu', '1.jpg', 'Mount Paektu, also known as Baekdu-san or Changbai Mountain, is a mountain located on the border between North Korea and China. With an elevation of 2,744 meters (9,003 feet), it is the highest mountain on the Korean Peninsula and holds significant cultural and historical importance in both countries.', 'Mount Paektu plays a crucial role in the culture and history of both North Korea and China. It is considered the birthplace of the Korean people and the sanctuary of Dangun, the legendary founder of the ancient Korean kingdom. Additionally, the mountain is linked to significant historical events and legends in Chinese culture.', 'Climbing Mount Paektu requires basic mountaineering skills and experience with harsh terrain and weather conditions. Thorough preparation and high endurance are necessary when facing the altitude and changing weather on the mountain.', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d11861.350449254027!2d128.06717587364747!3d41.993029437639564!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x5e34aef69343d173%3A0x29f9d45614652dce!2zTsO6aSBUcsaw4budbmcgQuG6oWNo!5e0!3m2!1svi!2s!4v1708950258747!5m2!1svi!2s\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe>', 'Located on the border between North Korea and China.', 'Mount Paektu and its surrounding area feature pristine landscapes with crystal-clear lakes and dense forests. The mountain is also a popular tourist destination, attracting visitors from both countries.', 'Climbing Mount Paektu not only entails risks from harsh weather conditions and rugged terrain but may also encounter restrictions regarding security and border regulations between the two countries. Mountaineering here may require coordination with authorities and strict control from relevant parties.', 0),
(40, 'Nanda Kot', '1.jpg', 'Nanda Kot is one of the high peaks in the Himalayas, located in the state of Uttarakhand, India. With an elevation of 6,861 meters (22,510 feet), it ranks among the highest peaks in the region. Nanda Kot has a rocky appearance with its summit consistently covered in snow and ice.', 'Nanda Kot has attracted the attention of explorers and mountaineers from around the world since the 19th century. The name \"Nanda Kot\" originates from Hindi, meaning \"Abode of Nanda,\" where \"Nanda\" refers to a goddess in Hindu mythology. The peak was first climbed in 1936 by a British-Indian expedition.', 'Climbing Mount Nanda Kot requires professional mountaineering skills and experience with the harsh terrain and weather conditions of the Himalayas. Thorough preparation, knowledge of mountaineering techniques, and safety measures are essential when undertaking this mountaineering expedition.', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d13781.831118679691!2d80.05778066758441!3d30.281026877014632!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x39a71da437487107%3A0x553655933ff2457d!2sNanda%20Kot!5e0!3m2!1svi!2s!4v1708950518537!5m2!1svi!2s\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe>', 'Situated in the state of Uttarakhand, India.', 'The area around Mount Nanda Kot is one of the most pristine and beautiful regions in the world, with diverse and abundant natural landscapes. The mountain is also a popular destination for trekking and mountaineering, attracting many adventure enthusiasts and nature explorers.', 'Climbing Mount Nanda Kot carries risks such as harsh weather conditions, altitude, the danger of snow and ice avalanches, landslide hazards, and medical emergencies. Thorough preparation and contingency planning are necessary before embarking on this mountaineering expedition.', 0),
(41, 'Rakaposhi', '1.jpg', 'Rakaposhi is one of the highest and most beautiful peaks in the Karakoram Range, located in northern Pakistan. With an elevation of 7,788 meters (25,551 feet), it ranks among the highest peaks in the region. Rakaposhi is known for its distinctive shape, with a smooth, rounded main summit and surrounding subsidiary peaks.', 'Rakaposhi has attracted the interest of explorers and mountaineers from around the world since the 19th century. The name \"Rakaposhi\" originates from the Shina language, a local language, meaning \"Shining Wall.\" The peak was first climbed in 1958 by a British-Pakistani expedition.', 'Climbing Mount Rakaposhi requires professional mountaineering skills and experience with the harsh terrain and weather conditions of the Karakoram Range. Thorough preparation, knowledge of mountaineering techniques, and safety measures are necessary when undertaking this mountaineering expedition.', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d12887.814356212655!2d74.47955707037333!3d36.14334328715632!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x38e62485a575f07f%3A0x2cf47d9a8ac25338!2sRakaposhi!5e0!3m2!1svi!2s!4v1708950711628!5m2!1svi!2s\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe>', 'Found in the north of Pakistan, near the border with China.', 'The area around Mount Rakaposhi is one of the most pristine and beautiful regions in the Karakoram Range, with diverse and abundant natural landscapes. The mountain is also a popular destination for trekking and mountaineering, attracting many adventure enthusiasts and nature explorers.', 'Climbing Mount Rakaposhi carries risks such as harsh weather conditions, altitude, the danger of snow and ice avalanches, landslide hazards, and medical emergencies. Thorough preparation and contingency planning are necessary before embarking on this mountaineering expedition.', 0),
(42, 'Ijen', '1.jpg', 'Mount Ijen is an active volcano located in East Java, Indonesia. Its highest peak reaches approximately 2,799 meters (9,183 feet) above sea level. One of the notable features of Mount Ijen is its unique volcanic crater lake at the summit, known for its turquoise-colored liquid and emitting hazardous gases from beneath the ground.', 'Mount Ijen has attracted the attention of tourists and scientists from around the world with its unique volcanic crater lake. It is not only a famous tourist destination but also a traditional sulfur mining area for local residents.', 'When embarking on a journey to climb Mount Ijen and visit its volcanic crater lake, travelers should possess basic trekking skills and be well-prepared for the mountain environment. Weather conditions can change rapidly and may be harsh, so ensuring safety is crucial.', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d53151.276767709955!2d114.19957709540527!3d-8.05116154518723!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x2dd149f2110ae607%3A0x7c04ef029d5e39bc!2sIjen!5e0!3m2!1svi!2s!4v1708950907582!5m2!1svi!2s\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe>', 'Located in the east of Java, Indonesia.', 'Some adventurous explorers may seek Mount Ijen as a wilderness retreat, drawn to the natural beauty of the volcano and its unique volcanic crater lake. However, it\'s important to remember that safety should always be the top priority when engaging in adventurous travel activities.', 'Hazards when visiting Mount Ijen include the risk of exposure to hazardous gases emitted from the volcanic crater lake and challenging trekking conditions on hilly terrain. Caution and adherence to safety guidelines are necessary to avoid dangerous situations when visiting this mountain.', 0);
