(43, 'Chu Yang Sin', '1.jpg', 'Chu Yang Sin Mountain is one of the tallest mountains in Vietnam, located in the southwestern Truong Son Range, within Dak Glei District, Kon Tum Province. With an elevation of approximately 2,422 meters, Chu Yang Sin Mountain offers the pristine and majestic beauty of the Central Highlands mountainous forests.', 'Chu Yang Sin Mountain is not only a significant natural landmark of the Central Highlands region but also holds cultural and spiritual value for local residents. It is considered a sacred site and often expected to be the location for religious ceremonies of ethnic minorities.', 'When embarking on a trekking journey to Chu Yang Sin Mountain, travelers need to have basic trekking skills and be well-prepared for the mountain environment. Knowledge of the weather conditions and terrain of this mountainous region is essential to ensure safety and success for the journey.', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d15586.412347552265!2d108.41371881240168!3d12.409483512167004!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x3171bd88b39c7293%3A0x77f52c85d7bb615e!2sChu%20Yang%20Sin!5e0!3m2!1svi!2s!4v1708951179903!5m2!1svi!2s\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe>', 'Positioned in the northwest of Vietnam.', 'Chu Yang Sin Mountain and its surrounding area are one of the tranquil and pristine destinations, suitable for those seeking refuge from everyday life and reconnecting with nature.', 'Hazards when trekking Chu Yang Sin Mountain include risks from harsh weather conditions, rugged terrain, and altitude. Thorough preparation and careful consideration are required before embarking on this mountain trekking journey.', 0),
(44, 'Kinabalu', '1.jpg', 'Mount Kinabalu is one of the highest mountains in Southeast Asia, located in Sabah, Malaysia. With an elevation of 4,095 meters (13,435 feet), it is the highest mountain in Malaysia and one of the most famous and popular peaks in the region. Kinabalu is part of Kinabalu Park, a UNESCO World Heritage Site.', 'Mount Kinabalu has attracted the attention of explorers and tourists from around the world. The summit was first conquered in 1851 by a British expedition led by Hugh Low. Kinabalu also holds cultural significance for local residents, considered a sacred and holy place.', 'Trekking Mount Kinabalu requires basic trekking skills and good preparation for the mountain environment. Travelers need to navigate through challenging mountain trails and ensure safety in harsh weather conditions.', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d15869.639595604165!2d116.54852396183338!3d6.0753342398437775!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x323ba2565e9224cb%3A0x2281c3fec0a9c05e!2sN%C3%BAi%20Kinabalu!5e0!3m2!1svi!2s!4v1708951699078!5m2!1svi!2s\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe>', 'Found in the state of Sabah, Malaysia.', 'The area surrounding Mount Kinabalu is an excellent destination for those seeking refuge and reconnecting with nature. Accommodations and camping facilities are provided within Kinabalu Park.', 'Hazards when trekking Mount Kinabalu include risks from harsh weather conditions, rugged terrain, and altitude. Additionally, there are risks from rockslides and climate factors. Thorough preparation and adherence to safety guidelines are crucial to ensure safety during the trek.', 0),
